 Priority=\"71\" SemiHidden=\"false\"\n   UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" Name=\"Colorful Shading Accent 6\"/>\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"72\" SemiHidden=\"false\"\n   UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" Name=\"Colorful List Accent 6\"/>\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"73\" SemiHidden=\"false\"\n   UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" Name=\"Colorful Grid Accent 6\"/>\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"19\" SemiHidden=\"false\"\n   UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"Subtle Emphasis\"/>\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"21\" SemiHidden=\"false\"\n   UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"Intense Emphasis\"/>\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"31\" SemiHidden=\"false\"\n   UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"Subtle Reference\"/>\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"32\" SemiHidden=\"false\"\n   UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"Intense Reference\"/>\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"33\" SemiHidden=\"false\"\n   UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"Book Title\"/>\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"37\" Name=\"Bibliography\"/>\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"39\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"TOC Heading\"/>\n </w:LatentStyles>\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 10]>\n<style>\n /* Style Definitions */\n table.MsoNormalTable\n	{mso-style-name:\"Table Normal\";\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\n	mso-style-priority:99;\n	mso-style-qformat:yes;\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\n	mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt;\n	mso-para-margin-top:0in;\n	mso-para-margin-right:0in;\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:10.0pt;\n	mso-para-margin-left:0in;\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\n	font-size:12.0pt;\n	font-family:\"Times New Roman\",\"serif\";}\n</style>\n<![endif]--></p>\n<p>On Sunday, June 19, former Army private David Laffer, 33, walked into a Medford pharmacy and opened fired. By all accounts he was on the search for prescription drugs. After an intensive manhunt, Laffer was arrested and held without bail for a crime that the Suffolk County Assistant District Attorney John Collins described as, &ldquo;the most cold-blooded robbery-homicide in Suffolk County history.&rdquo;</p>\n<p>The massacre took place at the Haven Drugs pharmacy where apparently David Laffer, disguising himself with a fake beard, glasses and baseball cap, calmly walked into the pharmacy on that Sunday morning at about 10:20 a.m. What happened next the investigators are trying to string together. What they do know is that four people were murdered in cold blood. While the drug store shooting was going down on the inside, outside Laffer&rsquo;s wife, Melinda Brady, was waiting to drive him away with the cache of stolen prescription drugs.</p>\n<p>Upon his arrest, David Laffer was found to have over 11,000 hydrocodone pills in his possession. This is the main ingredient in Vicodin one of the leading abused prescription painkillers. According to an official of the investigation, Laffer had also apparently stolen promethazine and cheratussin two of the main components in the recreational drug called Purple Drank.</p>\n<p><strong>Signs of a Troubling Drug Addiction</strong></p>\n<p>According to investigators, apparently that was the motive behind this senseless crime: scoring prescription drugs. Although it hasn&rsquo;t been confirmed yet that Laffer or his wife are addicts there are several indicating factors pointing in that direction. A person who becomes addicted to prescription drugs can exhibit signs of erratic behavior. Their thought process can become muddled. They can also suffer from extreme mood swings and experience bouts of high anxiety, hyperactivity and even develop dark thoughts of suicide.</p>\n<p>Quite often it is the dramatic withdrawal from a prescription drug addiction that forces addicts over the edge. When they&rsquo;ve reached a breaking point, an addict can act out in all manners of destructive behavior. People suffering from drug addictions have no trouble turning to crime to feed their habits. In fact, most prisoners currently incarcerated can trace their crimes back to some issue involving drugs whether that is selling, buying or stealing to support a habit.</p>\n<p>As tragic as this massacre is, it&rsquo;s also part of a national epidemic of drugstore robberies that can be attributed to prescription drug addicts looking for a fix. This is all the more unfortunate considering there are so many viable options for drug addiction treatment. An addict no longer has to suffer in silence or turn to crime. They can find genuine help which can lead them on the road to recovery.</p>\n<p><strong>Even Smart People Do Dumb Things While Addicted</strong></p>\n<p>Laffer served in the Army for eight years and was discharged in 2002. While in the service he worked as an intelligence analyst. This was a job which called for critical thinking skills and the ability to analysis even the minutest details of a piece of gathered intelligence. This is not a job for someone with a low I.Q. It was during a dinner with friends that David Laffer first met his future wife Melinda Brady. He would later propose to her during an Islanders game.</p>\n<p>As it often the case with a person who is living in the shadows of a drug addiction, no one saw this coming. Next-door neighbor Trish Bohlert was at David and Melinda&rsquo;s wedding.</p>\n<p>&ldquo;Something must have made him snap, because his personality, I can&#39;t picture him robbing a store, much less hurt people,&rdquo; she said.</p>\n<p>Another longtime neighbor, Zaida Ayala, said Laffer is &ldquo;a guy that I feel comfortable with, a guy that I could be out, 1 o&#39;clock in the morning in my backyard, and he could be in his backyard and I wouldn&#39;t run inside and go get my husband.&rdquo; She isn&rsquo;t convinced he is the shooter.</p>\n<p>Was It Drugs Or Love?</p>\n<p>Melinda Brady, 29, has been charged with robbery and obstructing governmental administration. She told reporters earlier that &quot;he did all of this&quot; for her. &quot;He was doing it because he lost his job and I was sick,&quot; Brady said as she was led from Suffolk police headquarters. Reporters noted that Melinda seemed addled and disheveled at the time of her arrest. Neither one of the couple has ever been in trouble with the law, but they were both high at the time of their arrest. Apparently, their drug of choice were prescription painkillers.</p>\n<p><strong>Not The First Horror in Suffolk County</strong></p>\n<p>The year was 1974 when the first horrific massacre took place in Suffolk County, New York. The tiny community of Amityville was rocked to its core when a seemingly pleasant and well-like husband shot to death six members of his family in the middle of the night. This bloody rampage was dubbed the Amityville Horror and was blamed on supernatural forces. The mass murder also spawned several films and book incarnations.</p>\n<p>Now, comes this new mass murder on Long Island. Medford, the scene of the tragedy, is a town just east of Amityville. The big difference this time around is that there seems to be no question as to the reasons behind these murders: The blame can be placed squarely on the devastating effects of a prescription drug addiction. The horrors associated with a drug addiction aren&rsquo;t relegated to affluent communities. These issues touch the lives of many people all across the country. Only with the proper treatment for addicts can these types of horrible events be prevented.</p>\n','Prescription Drug Robbery Leads To Mass Murder Horror','','draft','open','open','','','','','2011-06-24 20:59:11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?p=1103',10,'post','',0),(1107,1,'2011-08-11 01:23:17','2011-08-11 01:23:17','<p><span class=\"item\">There is no escaping the fact that alcohol or drug addiction can have a destructive impact on a person&#39;s life. Families, relationships and careers can all be impacted in the damaging wake of an addiction. That is why seeking professional recovery help is essential for those who are caught up in the throes of a substance abuse problem. However, just because a person has a desire to get clean and sober doesn&#39;t always mean they have the financial resources to enroll in rehabilitation care. As you explore the options for treatment for you or your loved one you can also explore the many options for paying for that treatment. Basically, there are three ways to finance a stay at rehab. These are through private insurance, obtaining government assistance or paying from your own savings.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"item\"><b style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">Health Insurance</b>: Many comprehensive health insurance policies cover the cost of rehabilitation treatment. Often you&#39;ll find these policies as part of an overall employee benefit package. In other words, you might be covered for rehab and not even know it. On the other hand, if you are buying your own insurance policy you might not include coverage for substance abuse treatment because you may think you&#39;ll never need it. While that might be true for many people it is often hard to predict which course our life or the life of our family members might take when it comes to substance abuse. If you currently have a health insurance plan and feel the need to explore rehabilitation care then call your policy representative and find out exactly what your options are. You might also be able to add coverage to your policy to cover these costs.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"item\"><b style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">Government Assistance</b>: Another option for paying for recovery treatment would be to seek out assistance from various government funded programs such as Medicare or Medicaid. It may be intimidating for someone to navigate through the bureaucratic red tape, but there is a light at the end of the proverbial tunnel especially if you can get the help. First, you should contact the treatment center you&#39;re thinking about checking into to see if they accept Medicare or Medicaid. If so they can probably provide you with the proper resources to determine if you qualify for that kind of assistance. You may find that a Medicare or Medicaid grant is on your own financial situation. If it is felt that you have assets to pay for the treatment yourself you might not get government assistance.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span class=\"item\"><b style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\">Paying Cash</b>: A final option is to pay for the treatment out of your own pocket. If you have accumulated savings or the means this is obviously a direct way of getting the help you or your loved one would need. However, that doesn&#39;t mean that a particular rehabilitation center won&#39;t work with you to make financial arrangements. You might be able to take out a loan to cover the cost of treatment or work out a payment plan with the facility as you would with a college tuition loan. Many rehab facilities understand that we are living in tough economic times and have developed payment options for individuals to help them get the assistance they need.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\nmso-outline-level:3\"><span class=\"item\">When you consider the overall devastating financial effects of an addiction problem, putting off treatment today because you can&#39;t afford it doesn&#39;t make a lot of sense. Help is available and help is out there. You just need to ask for it.</span><b><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\"> <br />\n	</span></b></p>\n','Financial and Insurance Options for Drug and Alcohol Addiction Treatment','','publish','open','open','','financial-and-insurance-options-for-drug-and-alcohol-addiction-treatment','','','2011-08-11 01:23:17','2011-08-11 01:23:17','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?p=1107',9,'post','',0),(1121,1,'2011-08-11 20:00:02','2011-08-11 20:00:02','<p>That was the question that haunted me like nothing i had ever feared before.&nbsp; All of my friends drink and party.&nbsp; What will i possibly do when they are out having fun? Do i really need to make a decision to have a social life or stay clean and sober? Well,&nbsp;it has&nbsp;been almost 4 years&nbsp;in sobriety and i have not&nbsp;shriveled&nbsp;up or become&nbsp;Captain. AA.&nbsp;&nbsp;Actually, my life is better in every aspect possible thanks to the fellowship&nbsp;and&nbsp;a whole bunch of willingness on my part.&nbsp; The fact is that&nbsp;I don&#39;t have to&nbsp;focus on being sober the rest of my life because the only thing that matters&nbsp;is right now.&nbsp; As cliche as that sounds, it works.&nbsp;&nbsp;The one question i will always ask is: How do you know if you don&#39;t give it a try? Now i know that question could be taken many different ways,&nbsp;but if you were&nbsp;standing where i was when i first got sober than you have already tried every possible concoction of substances and have already drownd every feeling you had with a nice bottle of whatever.&nbsp; Now is the time to find some solution that will&nbsp;last.&nbsp; For info&nbsp;on how to get sober or if you have any questions just give&nbsp;me a call at Soba Recovery Center.&nbsp; I know how you feel&nbsp;because i have been there.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>Stop existing and start living!!!</strong></p>\n<p>To&nbsp;find out&nbsp;where my journey in sobriety all started click the link</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://http://abcnews.go.com/Health/staying-sober-daniel-baldwin/story?id=4543817\">http://http://abcnews.go.com/Health/staying-sober-daniel-baldwin/story?id=4543817</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n','Sober in my 20\'s, Is My Life Over Or Just Beginning?','','publish','open','open','','sober-in-my-20s-is-my-life-over-or-just-beginning','','','2011-08-11 20:00:02','2011-08-11 20:00:02','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?p=1121',8,'post','',0),(1151,1,'2011-08-26 07:45:53','2011-08-26 07:45:53','<p>Thank you for your submission , we will contact with you shortly.</p>\n\n<script src=\'//d3c3cq33003psk.cloudfront.net/opentag-79694-1042532.js\' async defer></script>','Thank You','','publish','closed','closed','','thank-you','','','2011-08-26 07:45:53','2011-08-26 07:45:53','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?page_id=1151',26,'page','',0),(1169,1,'2012-01-12 18:24:49','2012-01-12 18:24:49','[gravityform id=\"3\" name=\"Verify Insurance\"]','Verify Your Insurance','','publish','open','open','','verify-insurance','','','2012-01-12 18:24:49','2012-01-12 18:24:49','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?page_id=1169',25,'page','',0),(1180,1,'2012-05-16 00:08:34','2012-05-16 00:08:34','','FECD0022-crop','','inherit','open','open','','fecd0022-crop','','','2012-05-16 00:08:34','2012-05-16 00:08:34','',0,'http://soba.localhost.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/FECD0022-crop.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1196,1,'2012-07-10 19:00:49','2012-07-10 19:00:49','If you\'re facing legal action as a result of a DUI or other drug or alcohol related charges, SOBA Recovery Center can help.  Our treatment center and sober living programs work with you and the courts to resolve your issue.  At SOBA recovery Center, we know how difficult it can be facing license revocation or prison time.  We have helped many people over the years with drug and alcohol cases, let us help you.  Often times, SOBA Recovery Center can will become an alternative sentencing to incarceration.\n\nWe provide the following services:\n\n<h2>Court Advocacy</h2>\n\nAs an ancillary service, an experienced court advocate will accompany you to your proceedings.  They will help in providing current status and progress reports directly to the courts.  Our staff has helped hundreds of people in resolving DUI and drug related cases.\n\nHighly experienced at navigating the complexities of the court system, your court advocate will work with lawyers, District Attorneys, public defenders, judges and probation officers to ensure that our clients receive court-ordered rehab as an alternative sentencing option\n\nWhat is usually included in this ancillary service:\n\nProfessional assessment\nProbation meeting coaching\nBackground of the Defendant/Social History\nAnalysis of Events Preceding the Offense\nAnalysis of Circumstances Surrounding the Current Offense\nAnalysis of Offense Conduct/Behavior\nReview of Prior Record/Criminal History\nFactors in Mitigation/Other Relevant Information\nComments/Objections to the Probation Department\'s Report\nAnalysis of Sentencing Law/Guidelines\nSummary Assessment &amp; Recommendations\nResearch Substance Rehab Placement Opportunities - Client Specific\n\n<h2>Residential Treatment</h2>\nSOBA Recovery Center is a state licensed treatment facility, At SRC, we provide individual, one-on-one therapy with renowned therapists who are fully versed in treating the underlying causes and conditions of addiction. Our therapists and doctors will assist you by providing the necessary tools to manage your life and address the issues that have plagued you. Once we have successfully treated the causes of your addiction, the likelihood of you remaining free from drugs and alcohol increase exponentially.\n\n<h2>Detox</h2>\nOur detox facility\n\n<h2>Sober Living</h2>\n\n<h2>Drug and Alcohol Testing</h2>\nWe are a licensed treatment center (both ADP and JAHCO accredited), so we are able to do all of our testing in-house.\n\n<h2>Outpatient Programs</h2>\nSOBA Recovery Center has day treatment and outpatient therapy for those based in and around Los Angeles.  We provide daily groups, one-on-one counseling, group therapy and family therapy.','DUI and Alternative Sentencing','','publish','closed','closed','','dui-and-alternative-sentencing','','','2012-07-10 19:00:49','2012-07-10 19:00:49','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?page_id=1196',24,'page','',0),(1206,1,'2012-09-21 20:15:50','2012-09-21 20:15:50','<img src=\"http://www.sobamalibu.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/los-angeles-drug-rehab.jpg\" alt=\"Los Angeles Drug Rehab\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1553\" />There’s nothing like a fresh morning at SOBA Recovery Center <a href=\"http://www.sobamalibu.com\">Los Angeles drug rehab</a> and detox facility with its crisp sea breeze that calms your mind and soothes your heart. It is comfortably nestled in one of the classiest real estate and beach fronts of Malibu. Sure to make a revitalizing treat are the picturesque scenery of natural flavors like gorgeous coastlines and lush terrain. With its prime location, unrivaled facilities and competitive services, this drug rehab ushers persons suffering from addiction to an unruffled and sober life full of hopes and opportunities for full recovery.\n\n<h2>What is detox?</h2>\n\nDrug detoxification refers to the safe and systematic process of withdrawing an individual from the use of addiction-causing drugs. Drinking alcohol or using drugs can eventually lead to physical dependence that chains a person from getting out of addiction. In some cases, drug addicts and alcoholics opt to discontinue the use of drugs and alcohol at their own phase. But, this may result to painful and life-threatening withdrawal symptoms or even death.\n\n<strong>The detox process has three stages:</strong>\n\n<strong>Patient Evaluation</strong>: SOBA Recovery Center’s doctors and medical staff shall conduct tests to determine the type and amount of substances present in your system. Further assessment shall also be made to establish the presence of other mental, emotional or behavioral problems aside from addiction and alcoholism. Examples of these conditions are bipolar disorder, borderline personality disorder, depression and post traumatic stress disorder. \n\n<strong>Stabilization</strong>: At this phase, you shall be guided by our staff throughout the whole detox process. SOBA Recovery Center has a medically-supervised detoxification program specifically designed for your condition. \n\nOur highly trained doctors, psychiatrists and addiction medicine specialists shall work hand in hand with your treatment counselors and other staff to ensure that you feel the least discomfort during this stage. We shall also exercise utmost patience and understanding in explaining to you the detox-related expectations and recovery outcomes. Our unique SOBA method not only eliminates harmful chemicals from your body but also balances your brain chemistry and invigorates you body through the \"Diet Free Life,\" program and exercise. \n\n<strong>Preparing the patient for recovery</strong>: This is also known as the stage of “guiding the patient into treatment.” Drug detox only eliminates your physical dependence from drugs and alcohol. To ensure complete recovery, our highly qualified staff shall help you deal with the psychological aspect of addiction by encouraging you to join our life-changing holistic and balanced SRC rehab programs.\n\n<h2>Why choose SOBA Recovery Center</h2>\n\nWe shall try to reverse the harmful effects of addiction in your life by implementing proven and effective detox procedures to give you a head start to recovery. We charge reasonable fees and offer convenient payment options.\n\nFor more information, on SOBA Recovery Center Los Angeles drug rehab and detox facility, simply call us at 866-547-6451or visit our contact page for a scheduled visit. Our friendly and knowledgeable staff shall also answer all your queries with regards to detox, alcoholism, drug addiction, as well as our <a href=\"http://www.sobamalibu.com/treatment-programs/drug-rehab-treatment/\">drug rehab</a> and treatment programs, facilities, staff and admission requirements.  \n\nMore Information:\nAddiction and Drug Abuse Prevention Tips <a href=\"http://www.samhsa.gov/prevention/\">SAMHSA</a>\n','Los Angeles Drug Rehab','','publish','closed','closed','','los-angeles-drug-rehab','','','2012-09-21 20:15:50','2012-09-21 20:15:50','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?page_id=1206',23,'page','',0),(1218,1,'2012-09-22 19:51:12','2012-09-22 19:51:12','<h2>Rehab That Accepts Aetna Insurance</h2>\n\nWith a challenging economy and rising cost of health care, having your treatment covered by Aetna insurance is a relief. Soba Recovery Center is a rehab that accepts Aetna insurance and provides easy payment options to make your stay cost-effective and non-stressful. We also understand that a good health plan shall help you pay for the significant cost of rehab stays and other qualified expenses. More so, <a href=\"http://www.sobamalibu.com/treatment-programs/drug-rehab-treatment/\">drug rehabilitation</a> can only be effective if you have all the support you need including financial backing. \n\n<h2>Aetna Insurance Rehab</h2>\n\nAetna insurance is provided by Aetna, Inc., a huge health care company in the country. It provides various insurance products directed to health care and associated services like behavioral health, medical management, disability plans and so forth. The company’s foremost mission is to provide its clients with easy access to reasonably-priced and first-rate health care. Aetna insurance has programs that assist its clients to go through drug rehabilitation. These include financial benefits and moral support. \n\n<h2>Aetna Payment Option and Coverage</h2>\n\nWhen the needs arise, Soba Recovery Center Aetna Insurance Rehab helps you tap into your Aetna benefits. Your Aetna coverage depends on your employer or individual policies, type of treatment, length of your stay at Soba Recovery Center and other circumstances. If the cost of the treatment covered under your existing Aetna plan exceeds the qualified amount, you can talk to our finance department for other payment alternatives.\nTreatment Programs for Aetna residents\n\nWe shall assist you in choosing the best treatment program suited for your needs.  We have the following treatment programs to help you achieve sobriety and deal with other underlying or co-occurring causes:\n\n1. Drug treatment service\n<ul>\n<li>Detox</li>\n<li>12 step program</li>\n<li>Art  therapy</li>\n<li>Equine therapy</li> \n<li>Music therapy</li>\n<li>Thrilling and challenging ropes course</li>\n</ul>\n\n2. Unique Alcohol Treatment Approach: It is composed of individually-tailored treatment plan that deals with your particular needs.\n\n3. SOBA Treatment\n\n4. Holistic Treatment\nWe have Board Certified and highly competent staff composed of the following: \n<ul>\n<li>Addictionologist</li>\n<li>Psychiatrist</li>\n<li>Clinical psychologist</li>\n<li>Acupuncturist</li>\n<li>Hypnotherapist</li>\n<li>Marriage and family therapist</li>\n<li>Nutritionist and Wellness Coach</li>\n<li>Personal Trainer</li>\n<li>Discharge and Aftercare planner</li> \n</ul>\n\nA change of scenery together with our treatment programs facilitates well-rounded recovery. The tranquil environment of Soba Recovery Center standing few meters away from Malibu Shore gives you an opportunity to see the world beyond the noise and stress of the city life. It may also inspire you to make an earnest self-appraisal to understand and accept your flaws and to resolve your issues with an open mind.  Remember that the road to sobriety starts with your first step- a step to wellness and freedom that comes from a calm mind and unwavering determination to recover.\n\nSoba Recovery Center has highly-qualified staff to talk to you about your financial concerns and types treatment covered by your Aetna insurance policy. We can also assist you in <a href=\"http://sobamalibu.com\">verifying your insurance</a>. Call us at 866-547-6451.\n\nMore information:\nAetnas Website : <a href=\"http://www.aetna.com/\">Aetna Insurance</a>\n','Aetna Insurance Rehab','','publish','closed','closed','','aetna-insurance-rehab','','','2012-09-22 19:51:12','2012-09-22 19:51:12','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?page_id=1218',22,'page','',0),(1224,1,'2012-09-22 20:18:44','2012-09-22 20:18:44','<div style=\"width:700px;padding:10px;margin:5px;\">\n<h2>United Health Care Rehab</h2>\n\nSOBA Recovery Center is a rehab that takes UnitedHealth insurance and offers flexible payment choices to help you avail of our successful programs on individual treatment covered by your policy. SRC also offers <a href=\"http://www.sobamalibu.com/treatment-programs/drug-rehab-treatment/\">rehabilitation services</a> to help you achieve complete recovery through our efficient staff and state of the art <a href=\"http://www.sobamalibu.com/facility-tour/\">facilities</a>. \n\n<h2>About United Healthcare</h2>\n\nUnitedHealthcare is one of the largest insurance providers in the US. It offers health care benefits to families and individuals through various health insurance plans. \n\nTo find out if your policy under UnitedHealth covers your drug rehabilitation, you can follow these two simple steps:\n\n1.  Schedule an appointment with SOBA Recovery Center. We will help you determine the types of rehabilitation services appropriate for your needs after our initial assessment. The findings may include the cause of the disorder, detoxification requirement, the treatment plan involved, the duration of treatment and the services you need. \n\n2.  Contact your insurance provider and discuss your financing alternatives and specific coverage. Or, you may also contact us at 866-547-6451 and our staff is available 24/7 to respond to your queries. \n\n<h2>Treatment covered by United Insurance</h2>\n\nPolicyholders receive plenty of policy benefits from United insurance. Some of the basic benefits include the following: \n\nDetox: SOBA Recovery Center implements highly specialized detoxification services to remove harmful substances caused by long term use of drugs and alcohol. Our detoxification method is JCAHO Accredited and carried out by our qualified and competent staff. For your physical wellness, we serve healthful meals carefully prepared by our professional chef. You also have a nutrition and fitness coach to help in your physical recovery. \n\nResidential Treatment: SOBA living is a social setting that houses individuals who are suffering or recovering from alcoholism and drug addiction. Our residents help each other achieve full recovery by sharing their experiences and providing encouragements to fellow residents in times of difficulties. Our semi-private or private cottages are available for you to occupy. In your own spot, you can relish the soft splash of the waves on the shore as you go to bed. The luxury of tranquility given by the charming seashore shall help you achieve calmness and a perfect sense of privacy. \n\nAside from our specialized treatment programs, we also offer social experiences that help our residents connect with each other through our special facilities like:\n\n<ul>\n<li>24-Hour Fitness Center</li>\n<li>Basketball Courts</li>\n<li>Half-Acre Par Course</li>\n<li>Outdoor Barbeque</li>\n<li>Poolside Cabanas</li>\n<li>Resort Style Pool</li>\n<li>Steam Rooms</li>\n<li>Tennis Courts</li>\n<li>The Beaches and Hills of Malibu!</li>\n<li>Zen Meditation Garden</li>\n</ul>\n\nOur social model for your treatment and recovery are specially designed to lessen any discomfort you are experiencing. We fully understand your condition and we want you to feel that we care and that we shall walk with you in every step of the way. \n\nAs a rehab that takes United insurance, we are not only concerned of your recovery but we also want to help you explore your financial options. If you have questions on treatment covered by United insurance or if you want your policy to be verified, call us at 866-547-6451. You can also contact us for more details. \n\nMore Information:\nUnited Health Care Website : <a href=\"http://www.uhc.com/\">United Health Care</a>\n</div>','United Health Care Insurance Rehab','','publish','closed','closed','','united-health-care-insurance-rehab','','','2012-09-22 20:18:44','2012-09-22 20:18:44','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?page_id=1224',21,'page','',0),(1229,1,'2012-09-22 20:34:36','2012-09-22 20:34:36','SOBA Malibu Recovery Center drug rehab is a <a href=\"http://www.sobamalibu.com/treatment-programs/holisitic-treatment-explained/\">holistic sober community</a> that incorporates DBT therapy, detox, and other treatment programs to help you stop drug and alcohol abuse in the most comfortable way possible. \n\n<h2>Causes of continued drug and alcohol use</h2> \n\nSome people start using drugs and drinking alcohol with the thought that anyone can quit anytime. Others shun the idea of enrolling in a drug treatment program or entering into a sober community with the belief that they have the ability to control their addiction impulse without help. However, studies showed that changes in the brain occur once a person uses drugs or alcohol for a long time. These drug and alcohol-induced alteration make it difficult for a person to control his or her urge to consume alcohol or use drugs despite its harmful effects. This failure to control this impulse is the distinctive symptom of addiction. \n\nAdditionally, there are factors that prevent a person from sustaining abstinence and increase the risk of relapse like the following:\n\n<ul>\n<li>Work-related stress or problems in school</li>\n<li>Family problems like divorce, sexual or emotional abuse, financial problems and the like</li>\n<li>Underlying mental health problems like borderline personality disorder, bipolar disorder, etc.</li> \n<li>Pain due to physical ailment</li>\n<li>Drug addict or alcoholic friends or relatives</li>\n<li>Exposure to an environment that reminds them of former drug use or alcoholism</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Health effects of drug addiction and alcoholism</h2>\n\nAside from this brain pattern, alcoholism and drug addiction causes significant harm to your health, relationships and career. \nThe following are the most common physical effects of drug addiction\n\n<ul>\n<li>Pinpoint or dilated Pupils</li>\n<li>Hypertension</li>\n<li>Erratic mood swings and abnormal increase or decrease of energy\n<li>Increased Heart Rate</li>\n<li>Appetite changes</li>\n<li>Paranoia</li>\n<li> Anxiety</li>\n<li>Unreasonable violence of rage</li>\n<li>Breathing problems</li>\n<li> Dehydration</li>\n<li>Abnormal sweating</li>\n</ul>\n\nDrug addiction and alcoholism cause any or all of the following long-term effects:\n\n<ul>\n<li>Depression</li>\n<li>Brain damage</li>\n<li>Increased risk of cancer, hypertension, stroke, HIV, Hepatitis A and C, and other diseases of the liver</li>\n<li>Impotence</li>\n<li>Hallucinations/paranoia</li>\n<li>Apathy or lack of motivation</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>SOBA Recovery Center Holistic Sober Community intervention</h2>\n\nGetting out of these vicious habits requires self-determination and support from knowledgeable and caring professionals. We at SOBA Recovery Center understand the biological and psychological component of alcoholism and drug addiction. Upon conducting several tests to assess your condition we shall implement individualized treatment plan to meet your needs. Our renowned therapists shall work with you in resolving the issues that bother you during the one-on-one therapy sessions. We shall also help you explore the different treatment methods like detox, DBT therapy and other programs offered by our holistic sober community. What’s more, we do all these things in the most relaxed and comfortable beach setting in Malibu, a paradise drug rehab and sober community to help you start all over again. \n\nExperience freedom from addiction and live your life in the best way possible. Take the first step by calling us today, at 866-547-6451. \n\nOther Resources:\n\n<a href=\"http://www.drugabuse.gov/about-nida/other-resources\">National Institute On Drug Abuse</a>\n<a href=\"http://www.drugfree.org/\">Parents Dealing With Teen Drug Abuse</a>\n<a href=\"http://www.phrma.org/rxabuse\"> Prescription Drug Abuse Resources</a>\n<a href=\"http://www.whitehouse.gov/ondcp/state-map\">Office Of National Drug Control Policy</a>\n<a href=\"http://www.casacolumbia.org/templates/Home.aspx\">Columbia University National Center On Addiction and Drug Abuse</a>\n<a href=\"http://free.ed.gov/subjects.cfm?subject_id=61&toplvl=60\">Federal Resources For Educational Excellence</a>\n\n','Drug Rehab','','publish','closed','closed','','drug-rehab','','','2012-09-22 20:34:36','2012-09-22 20:34:36','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?page_id=1229',20,'page','',0),(1233,1,'2012-09-22 20:42:43','2012-09-22 20:42:43','<h2>Court Ordered Drug Treatment Center</h2>\n\nSOBA Recovery center is a drug treatment center that welcomes court advocacy for drug abusers charged with offenses. We are also known as a <a href=\"http://www.sobamalibu.com/los-angeles-drug-rehab/\">Los Angeles drug rehab</a> that implements proper drug treatment for persons involved in substance-related crimes.\n\n<h2>How court advocacy works</h2>\n\nWe at SOBA Recovery Center recognize the destructive effects of substance abuse on your brain.  Examples are weakened or faulty reasoning, problems in your behaviors and violent tendencies. \n\nSometimes, you may fall into chemical dependency and get involved in crimes because of your condition. If you will be placed in jail without any access to a treatment program to take care of your addiction, you may still commit the same legal problems upon serving your jail term. For this reason, the government recognized court advocacy as a way to help you learn from your mistakes and to get back on track. In this way, you can be a fully-recovered person and a productive member of the society.\n\nCourt advocates lend a hand to individuals arrested for crimes that are connected to drugs and addictive conditions. They work with lawyers and clients in mapping out an-outpatient rehab program that will decrease court sentence while ensuring that the court requisites are observed. Once you receive a court ordered program you can enroll in SOBA Recovery Center Los Angeles drug rehab.\n\n<h2>Benefits of court-ordered rehab</h2>\n\nInside the rehab, you can deal with your underlying conditions and experience the rehabilitation process. You will learn to be responsible for your own actions.  With proper treatment programs, support and guidance, you will pull yourself through and stay on the path of recovery. \nCourt-ordered rehab has the following benefits:\n<ul>\n<li>It will help you avoid spending your time in jail. Instead of serving your sentence, you will be allowed to enter a drug rehab and go through a drug treatment plan that will address the underlying issues of your chemical dependence. </li>\n<li>You can break free from drug addiction. At SOBA Recovery Center, we shall evaluate your condition and help you discover the factors that cause or influence your addictive behaviors. We shall also carry out an <a href=\"http://www.sobamalibu.com/treatment-programs/\">individualized treatment program</a> that will help you take responsibility for your decisions and actions.</li> \n\n\nWe break this plan into several parts:\n\n<ol>\n<li>Physical healing: It may involve detoxification and management of withdrawal symptoms.</li> \n<li>Physical fitness: We have personal trainers to increase your stamina and improve your body coordination. There are different types of exercises and therapies that will help you stay fit and recover what your body has lost due to chemical dependence. </li>\n<li>Nourishment: At SOBA, our culinary staff shall supplement your medication, therapies and fitness program with delicious and highly-nutritious food to nourish your body.</li>\n\n\n<li>You will be less likely to commit another criminal offense.  SRC drug treatment center is a Los Angeles drug rehab that adapts the holistic treatment approach in dealing with substance abuse. As we treat your addiction, we shall also treat any co-existing mental condition that affects your recovery. With your determination and with our highly competent staff, you can achieve total recovery.</li> \n</ul>\n\nAllow us to help you by calling 866-547-6451 today!\n','Court Ordered Drug Treatment Center','','publish','closed','closed','','court-ordered-drug-treatment-center','','','2012-09-22 20:42:43','2012-09-22 20:42:43','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?page_id=1233',19,'page','',0),(1245,1,'2012-09-22 21:10:51','2012-09-22 21:10:51','<div style=\"width:700px;padding:10px;margin:5px;\">\n<h2>DUI Alcohol Treatment Center</h2>\n\nSOBA Recovery Center is an alcohol addiction treatment facility that gives DUI help to individuals with alcohol problems. Our facility is cuddled in one of the most scenic locations in Malibu. It has a direct access to the beach and sumptuous view of the relaxing coast. While you undergo rehabilitation program according to the court order, you and your family can enjoy the luxurious treatment at SRC. \n\n<h2>DUI arrest and rehabilitation</h2>\n\nDUI arrest is one of the signs of alcoholism and unhealthy behaviors. It can also be an indication of one’s emotional instability, impaired reasoning and lack of accountability. All of these characteristics may be regarded as a warning sign of a more serious problem that can cause further damage to the person involved. \nCourt-ordered rehabilitation for DUI clients aim to help you-\n\n<ul>\n<li>Equip yourself with necessary skills to deal with situations that would normally prompt you to drink alcohol.</li> \n<li>Discover behavior patterns or situations that lead you to alcohol use</li>\n<li>Regain control over your drinking impulses</li>\n<li>Choose an alcohol-free lifestyle</li>\n</ul>\n\nAt SRC, we provide individualized care plan to make an early intervention to deal with serious underlying causes of DUI and strategies that will improve your lifestyle.\n\nSome of the valuable benefits provided at SOBA Recovery Center for clients with DUI charges include the following:\n\n<ul>\n<li>Quality detox services: We have competent and specially trained staff to supervise your detoxification process in our JCAHO-Accredited detox facility. We shall also take care of your withdrawal symptoms and help you restore your physical well-being by incorporating good nutrition and strength building techniques to your treatment plan.</li>\n<li>Effective one-on-one and group counseling: We have doctors, therapists and other specialists to help you determine the cause of your alcohol dependence. After thorough evaluation, our staff shall conduct individualized counseling sessions that will facilitate healing of your mind. We also have different types of intervention to address dual diagnosis and other psychological problems. Aside from individual counseling, you may be encouraged to join a group counseling session.  This will allow you to share your struggles and fears with people who also go through the same problems. We shall also guide you through the recovery process to help you avoid relapse.</li> \n<li>Specifically designed treatment plan to address your mental and behavioral issues while treating your drinking problem: SOBA Recovery Center creates a unique plan for every client because we understand that every person has unique circumstances. Each step of the treatment program is designed according to the degree of your drinking problems, the causes of your problematic behaviors, and other factors that lead to your DUI charges.</li>\n</ul>\n \nRehabilitation is achieved through a well-informed decision to get well based on the in-depth knowledge of your DUI condition and your determination to live a healthy lifestyle. It is our goal to help you live a good quality of life through our best efforts of providing holistic rehabilitation for people with alcohol and drug problems.\n\nFor more details on DUI help and family support for individuals with alcohol problems, call us at 866-547-6451.\n</div>','DUI Alcohol Treatment Center','','publish','closed','closed','','dui-alcohol-treatment-center','','','2012-09-22 21:10:51','2012-09-22 21:10:51','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?page_id=1245',18,'page','',0),(1249,1,'2012-09-23 19:41:43','2012-09-23 19:41:43','<h2>Addiction Treatment Centers</h2>\n\nIf you are looking for detox and <a href=\"http://www.sobamalibu.com\">addiction treatment centers</a> that conduct individual therapy and group therapy, SOBA Malibu is the best place to start with. We use exceptional and proven counseling therapy techniques to address the psychological side of addiction that aims to establish lifelong recovery. \n\n<h2>Two common types of counseling</h2>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.sobamalibu.com/treatment-programs/\">Individual therapy</a>: It refers to one-on-one sessions with your personal counselor. This is conducted in a private place to promote open communication. During this meeting, you and your therapist can explore the causes of your alcohol abuse or drug addiction. Once you identify the things that trigger your chemical dependence, you and your therapist can develop techniques to deal with them.\n\n<a href=\"http://www.sobamalibu.com/treatment-programs/\">Group Therapy</a>: It is a gathering of fellow alcoholics or drug addicts under the supervision of a licensed counselor or therapist. All of them can share their personal stories and suggestions to help attain recovery.\n\n<h2>Benefits of counseling</h2>\n\nSome treatment centers allege that you can achieve total cure through detoxification. We disagree with this idea because we believe that a person can only achieve total recovery when your mind, body and spirit are in total harmony. For this reason, we implement effective counseling therapy sessions to help us make a holistic treatment plan that specifically targets every aspect of your condition. \n\nEffective counseling sessions conducted under the supervision of our highly renowned counselor offers the following benefits: \n\nIt allows you speak out your concerns without fear of being ridiculed. SOBA Malibu is a place where you can talk openly about everything with regards to your recovery. If you have not been honest with yourself for a long time, you can use individual and group therapy sessions to speak truthfully about anything that bothers you. By being open about your thought and feelings, you can experience a therapeutic release from your fears, unhealthy thoughts and even chains from your past.  \nYour therapists can determine the deep-seated causes of your addiction:  Individual and group therapy sessions can help your therapists in mapping out the presence of dual diagnosis or other disorders. As your hidden thoughts and conflicts surface, they can also device a unique treatment plan to concentrate on every detail of your chemical dependence. \n\nIt gives you a chance to create a support network: During the group counseling sessions, you will have a opportunity to share your feelings and offer encouragement to fellow drug addicts or alcoholics in recovery. SOBA Malibu is a place where people in recovery can identify their situations and experiences with fellow residents. While they make progress in their recovery process, they also learn to share their experiences with others who need comfort and support. So, if you are a newcomer you will feel inspired with the stories of recovering addicts and you shall experience the unconditional support from people who understand your situation.\n\nCompared to other addiction treatment centers and detox facilities, SOBA Malibu offers unique group therapy and individual therapy experiences that will help you get on the path to recovery. Call us at 866-547-6451 for urgent counseling and assessment. \n','Addiction Treatment Centers','','publish','closed','closed','','addiction-treatment-centers','','','2012-09-23 19:41:43','2012-09-23 19:41:43','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?page_id=1249',17,'page','',0),(1253,1,'2012-09-27 08:49:46','2012-09-27 08:49:46','\n<h2>DBT Rehab</h2>\nSOBA Malibu is an alcohol rehab and <a href=\"http://www.sobamalibu.com\">residential treatment facility</a> that implements <a href=\"http://www.sobamalibu.com/treatment-programs/holisitic-treatment-explained/\">holistic</a> approach that incorporates dialectical behavioral therapy in our individual therapy, group therapy and family therapy sessions. Our state of the art amenities are specifically designed to promote cognitive behavior therapy. It also aims to support your recovery during your <a href=\"http://maliburecoverycenter.com/services/soba-detox/\">seven day detox</a>, inpatient treatment or residential treatment.\n<h2>Components of Dialectical Behavior Therapy</h2>\nDialectical Behavioral Therapy is an integrated approach to facilitate the complete healing of your mind and to change your behaviors. It follows three essential steps:\n\n1. Cognitive behavior therapy:\n\nThe main feature of DBT is to help you learn new sets of behaviors that can range from your way of thinking, action or emotions. It implements four strategies:\n\nCognitive therapy: You will learn to recognize your negative thoughts and evaluate its patterns. In so doing, you can substitute them with constructive thoughts that will help align your perspectives and see things in a realistic way.\n\nContingency management: Your therapist shall help identify your maladaptive behaviors and its harmful effects. By having a clear understanding of punishment and reward based on your behaviors, you will be able to transform your behavior in an optimistic way.\n\nExposure: During the therapy session, you will be exposed to the things that you are afraid of. It may include situations, feelings or thoughts that you used to fear or avoid in the past.\n\nSkills training: At SOBA Malibu, you will be encouraged to join skills groups that will teach you to gain control of your emotions. You may also do homework assignments that will help you gain a deeper understanding of yourself and the process that you go through. Role playing activities are also implemented to help you find constructive ways to relate with other people.\n\n2. Offering Validation and encouraging change of behaviors: In order to reinforce change of behaviors, our licensed therapists shall offer validation to patients. It will lessen the stress caused by the demands of recovery. Validation simply means that your therapist is saying that you are getting there and that your actions seem sensible. However, it does not necessarily imply that the therapist agrees that your action is the best way to deal with the situation.\n\n3. Therapists and patients work together to handle inconsistencies. There are several contradictions that the patient has to deal with like self acceptance and the need for change. DBT is founded on the assumption that there is a connection between everything and that opposite things can be put together to make a positive change. DBT asserts that change is unavoidable and that it is a constant process. During this phase, your therapist shall make necessary interventions to help you accept your weaknesses and your need for change.\n<h2>Summary of DBT Benefits</h2>\nAlcohol rehab, seven day detox, and inpatient treatment or residential treatment will be successful if family therapy, group therapy, or individual therapies for people with addiction problems use DBT.\n\nTo sum it up, Dialectical behavior therapy has three major benefits:\n<ul>\n 	<li>It helps you develop skills to cope up with daily stressors</li>\n 	<li>It regulates your emotions</li>\n 	<li>It improves your relationships with other people</li>\n</ul>\nCall us at 866-547-6451 for 24/7 counseling services.','DBT Rehab','','publish','closed','closed','','dbt-rehab','','','2012-09-27 08:49:46','2012-09-27 08:49:46','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?page_id=1253',16,'page','',0),(1259,1,'2012-09-27 08:57:31','2012-09-27 08:57:31','SOBA Malibu inpatient treatment facility and residential treatment is an excellent place to avail of seven day detox, alcohol rehab and other treatment programs for people with addiction. Our inpatient treatment program offers a wide array of benefits that will increase your chance to have a successful recovery. In addition to our first class detox facility, we also use different counseling sessions like family therapy, group therapy and individual therapy. We have modern facilities, exceptional staff and luxurious amenities to accelerate your recovery. \n\n<h2>Inpatient treatment Benefits</h2>\n\nThe following are the benefits of inpatient treatment programs:\n\nMedically managed detoxification procedure: Skilled and highly-trained professionals shall be in-charge of your medical detox. This is advisable for patients with addiction to cocaine, prescription drugs, amphetamines and opiates because of the withdrawal symptoms associated with those drugs. During the inpatient detox procedure, the medical team shall conduct constant monitoring of dangerous signs of withdrawal, like heart attack and coma. The medical staff shall also administer medications, if needed. \nSome of the service-related benefits of inpatient detox also include:\n\n<ul>\n<li>Round the clock nursing services</li>\n<li>The physician or psychiatrist visits the detox patient on a daily basis</li>\n<li>Close and crucial monitoring of serious withdrawal symptoms</li>\n</ul>\n\nSOBA Malibu is a peaceful and calm hospital alternative when it comes to detox procedures. We offer our state of the art detox facility at a reasonable price which is comparable to the prevailing hospital rate. Depending on the protocol of your attending detox physician, your length of stay can vary from five to seven days, or more. We also ensure privacy and 100% confidentiality to our patients.\n\nCounseling and Behavior Therapy: We do not end with the detox itself. Instead, we proceed to the second part of our treatment program which addresses the most important part of your recovery-the healing of your mind. Once your body is cleansed from harmful drugs and toxins, our treatment team can already begin to work on the underlying causes of your addiction. We have psychiatrists, psychologists and celebrated therapists to help you uncover the issues masked behind your maladaptive behaviors and addictive patterns. Some of therapy sessions include family therapy, group therapy and individual therapy. As the counseling session and treatment-related activities push through, you will learn more about your condition and the things that you need to do to deal with them. You will also learn positive coping mechanisms, stress management techniques, and positive behavior patterns through our specialized counseling sessions and different activities included in your treatment plan.  \n\nAftercare services: We want you to live a normal life after you finish seven day detox, inpatient treatment or alcohol rehab program. We have programs to usher you to a new lifestyle that will help you fight triggering factors of addiction. You can continue to live in our residential treatment facility or <a href=\"http://maliburecoverycenter.com/services/sober-living/\">sober living</a> community where you will experience transitional living in the most comfortable and compassionate way possible. \n\nYou can call us at 866-547-6451 and we shall discuss with you the possibilities of having a sober living arrangement right at your own private or semi-private cottage in the stunning SOBA Malibu beachfront location in California. \n','Alcohol Rehab','','publish','closed','closed','','alcohol-rehab','','','2012-09-27 08:57:31','2012-09-27 08:57:31','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?page_id=1259',15,'page','',0),(1262,1,'2012-09-27 09:04:52','2012-09-27 09:04:52','Heroin addiction treatment is a complex process that entails the skills of highly qualified medical professionals and unwavering dedication from the medical staff in an opiate addiction rehab. At SOBA Malibu, we make a personal program for every person addicted to heroin. It is fortified with medically-advanced detoxification procedures, tried and tested behavioral and cognitive therapies and other activities that are designed to address every detail of your heroin addiction.\n\n<h2>Heroin and its effects on your health</h2>\n\nHeroin is one of the most commonly abused opiate drugs in the country. It is a black, brown or white powdered opiate drug which is usually smoked, snorted or injected by the users.  When the drug enters your brain it converts to morphine. Next, it attaches to opiod receptors which are located in the brain and the body. The most affected opiod receptors are those that are involved in the reward and pain response, stimulation, breathing and blood pressure.\nAs a result, the person using heroin experiences the following:\n\n<ul>\n<li>Alternating wakefulness and drowsiness </li>\n<li>Difficulty of breathing or coma in case of heroin overdose</li>\n<li>Distorted thoughts or mental function</li>\n<li>Dry mouth</li>\n<li>Euphoria or a sudden surge of ecstatic feelings</li>\n<li>Warm skin flushes</li>	\n</ul>\n\nA person becomes addicted to heroin because tolerance develops with habitual use. Thus, a person needs more dosage to achieve the same effects of the drugs.\nThe following are the serious complications of heroin abuse: \n\n<ul>\n<li>Abscesses</li>\n<li>Collapsed veins (in users who use inject heroin)</li>\n<li>Fatal overdose</li>\n<li>Infection of the heart valves and linings</li>\n<li>Infectious diseases (for needle users) like hepatitis, HIV and AIDS</li>\n<li>Kidney disease</li>\n<li>Liver problems</li>\n<li>Pneumonia and other pulmonary complications</li>\n<li>Spontaneous abortion</li>\n<li>Death</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Heroin addiction treatment</h2>\n\nSOBA Recovery Center is a residential treatment facility and an opiate addiction rehab. We have specialized treatment programs for persons who are addicted to heroin. Unlike other rehabs, we make a personal and individualized treatment plan to get to the bottom of your heroin addiction. We understand that people have many reasons why they get into heroin dependence. For this purpose, we would like to address the underlying factors that trigger your addiction, including co-existing psychological and behavioral problems. Aside from focusing on the causes, we shall also help you to break free from addiction through our holistic treatment approach.\n\nIn every step of the way, our counselors, therapists and medical experts shall provide dedicated and caring services to help you get back on your feet. We treat your addiction and expose the triggering factors that caused it. At the same time, we also teach you how to cope up with the daily stressors so that you can avoid relapse.\n\nMoreover, we have personal trainers and nutrition experts to ensure that your body will be as strong as your mind when you leave SOBA Malibu \n\nTo top it all, our heroin addiction treatment and opiate addiction rehab offers a luxury living experience near the coast of the captivating Malibu Shore.  Experience total healing of your body, mind and spirit by enrolling in our treatment program for persons addicted to heroin. Call us at 866-547-6451 for more information. \n','Heroin Addiction Treatment','','publish','closed','closed','','heroin-addiction-treatment','','','2012-09-27 09:04:52','2012-09-27 09:04:52','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?page_id=1262',14,'page','',0),(1268,1,'2012-10-09 09:11:19','2012-10-09 09:11:19','<p class=\"lead\">People who became addicted to heroin will greatly benefit from the focused and personalized treatment methods of SOBA Malibu. It is composed of seven day heroin detox, one-on-one therapy and other specialized treatment modalities specifically designed for every patient.</p>\n\n<h2>Heroin Withdrawal Symptoms</h2>\nIndividuals who regularly abuse heroin may develop tolerance and physical dependence on the drugs. Consequently, withdrawal symptoms may occur when a person stops cold turkey or at least six hours from the last heroin use. The intensity and duration of withdrawal may vary from one to seven days. Others also experience Post Withdrawal Symptoms which may last from several weeks to months.\n<strong>\nIntense cravings for heroin:</strong> Heroin addicts want to reduce the withdrawal symptoms and to re-experience the pleasure brought about by the drugs. This is a distinctive characteristic of people withdrawing from addictive substances.\n\n<strong>Mood changes:</strong> People withdrawing from heroin and other opiate drugs often complaining of irritability, anxiety, depression and mood swings. This dysphoric mood is due to the euphoric effects of heroin. These feelings usually pass after the withdrawal phase.\n\n<strong>Rebound effect:</strong> Heroin addicts complain of back and leg pains and increased sensitivity to pain during the withdrawal stage. This complaint is rooted on the effect of pain-blocking effects of heroin.\n\n<strong>Excess body fluids:</strong> There will be an increased production of body fluids like runny nose, tears and sweat during heroin withdrawal.\n\n<strong>Stomach troubles:</strong> Diarrhea and loose bowel movement is the body’s natural reaction to heroin withdrawal. Stomach pain may also occur due to spasms on the digestive system.\n\n<strong>Nausea and vomiting:</strong> Some heroin addicts consider this as the most distressful aspect of withdrawal because it prevents them from enjoying their food. It is also very uncomfortable and tiring.\n\n<strong>Fever:</strong> It is important to seek medical treatment when your temperature exceeds 40 C especially if you have serious medical condition.\n\n<strong>Restlessness:</strong> A person may experience agitation especially during the most intense period of withdrawal.\n\n<strong>Insomnia:</strong> Sleep problems are very common to people experiencing heroin withdrawal. Yawning is also commonly observed during this phase because of lack of sleep.\n\nAlthough withdrawal from heroin may cause discomfort, most of these reactions are not life-threatening. However, it is important to find a good seven day heroin detox facility with one-on-one therapy, and several programs of treatment for heroin addiction.\n<h2>SOBA Malibu Heroin Detox Facility</h2>\nIndividuals who want to recover from heroin addiction may be apprehensive to stop heroin abuse because of the discomforts of withdrawal. At SOBA Malibu, we take care of the physical aspect of your heroin withdrawal while we ensure that your body can recover from its pernicious effects. We have a fully equipped detox facility with competent staff to detoxify your body. We also serve good food carefully prepared by professional chef to nourish your body and to replenish the nutrients lost by the detox process and improper diet. After the heroin detox, you can continue with the holistic treatment program for recovering drug addicts. You may also choose from several treatment programs and activities that will help you recover permanently from heroin addiction.\n\nFor more information on seven day heroin detox, one-on-one therapy, and other treatment for heroin addiction, call us at <strong>866-547-6451</strong>.','Heroin Drug Rehab','','publish','closed','closed','','heroin-drug-rehab','','','2012-10-09 09:11:19','2012-10-09 09:11:19','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?page_id=1268',13,'page','',0),(1273,1,'2012-10-09 09:16:21','2012-10-09 09:16:21','<p class=\"lead\">Court advocacy can help individuals with DUI and substance related crimes to avail of alternative sentencing or court-mandated rehab at SOBA Malibu.</p>\n\n<h2>How SOBA Recovery Center DUI Rehab Can Help You</h2>\nPossible reduction of charges: Attending a DUI rehab may prove to the judge in-charge of your case that you are committed to recover from dependence to alcohol. The court may reduce the sentence to a fine or to a shorter period in jail if-\n<ul>\n 	<li>You started to attend a treatment program in a DUI rehab before your scheduled court hearing, or-</li>\n 	<li>You completed a recovery program before the court hearing date</li>\n</ul>\nGain control of yourself: Regardless of the court decision, DUI rehab programs can help you pull yourself through alcohol dependence. There are many people who live in constant fear and pain due to alcohol problems. Their inability to control their cravings for alcohol cause relative problems to their health, family and society. As a result, they may feel helpless and unable to run their lives in the best way possible. With a good DUI rehab that has reasonable DUI costs, you can take the rein of your destiny by starting the course to recovery at SOBA Malibu DUI Rehab.\n\nBetter living condition: Where do you want to serve sentence? Isn’t our luxury DUI rehab and alternative sentencing facility more comfortable than the jail cells and streets in the community? Although there are advantages in doing community service, you will only pay your dues in the society but you will not get better. Remember that the most important component of rehabilitation is your physical and psychological healing that result from an effective rehabilitation program. Without treatment, you are merely paying what you owe to the society but you are still indebted to yourself. Freedom from any type of addiction is your responsibility to yourself.\n\nFor this cause, drug advocacy intends to provide individuals with court cases due to alcohol abuse or drug addiction an opportunity to go through rehabilitation in a DUI rehab.\n<h2>Benefits and Amenities of SOBA Malibu DUI rehab</h2>\n<ul>\n 	<li><strong>Unique treatment program that helps you live an addiction-free life:</strong> We use the holistic treatment approach that focus on the healing of your body, mind and spirit.</li>\n 	<li><strong>Luxurious setting with reasonable DUI costs</strong></li>\n 	<li><strong>Caring and friendly environment that supports personal healing</strong></li>\n 	<li><strong>Emotional support network:</strong> We have group therapies and related activities that are designed to give you the emotional support you need especially during the toughest times of your recovery. SOBA Malibu also offers family therapy and counseling to help you and your family deal with your conditions and its impact on your relationships.</li>\n 	<li>We also have a caring alumni community which is known for its active support network to all former residents of SOBA Recovery Center.</li>\n 	<li>Fun and exciting activities like swimming, surfing and rope activities.</li>\n</ul>\nOur counselors can discuss to you DUI costs and other concerns related to court advocacy programs. Call us at <strong>866-547-6451</strong>to know more about court mandated rehab and alternate sentencing options.','DUI Drug and Alcohol Rehab','','publish','closed','closed','','dui-drug-and-alcohol-rehab','','','2012-10-09 09:16:21','2012-10-09 09:16:21','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?page_id=1273',12,'page','',0),(1279,1,'2012-10-09 09:20:32','2012-10-09 09:20:32','SOBA Malibu Los Angeles detox center is a facility that you can trust when it comes to seven day detox, and other drug and alcohol detox process. Compared to stay at home detox, we offer excellent and effective inpatient detox through our modern facility and skilled staff. \n\n<h2>Drug and alcohol detox process</h2>\n \nDrug and alcohol detox process begins at the moment you abruptly stop using drugs. As a result, you may experience withdrawal symptoms which are the opposite effects of the substance you used. The severity of withdrawal symptoms is dependent on three major factors:  regularity of use, type of substance and length of use. Other factors include your emotion, mind set and physical condition.\n\nDetoxification seeks to eliminate the toxins from the body. These toxins refer to chemicals or impurities that prevent or delay normal body functions and cause disease or congestion in the body. Such obstruction normally affects body systems which are responsible for removing toxic materials from the body like urinary, lymph and circulatory system. Other organs involved in the elimination of toxins also include the liver, colon and other organs. \nDetoxification period\n\nDetox period means the length of time required to eliminate the active toxins from the body. It may last from five or seven days to a number of months. In most cases, proper medications are used to support the detoxification of patients who are withdrawing from alcohol, opiates and other addictive drugs. Medically supervised detoxification is usually required for patients with severe withdrawal symptoms to avoid fatal complications. Depending on the results of your evaluation, your doctors shall prescribe stay at home detox or inpatient rapid detox or seven day detox to clean up your system.\n\nAt SOBA Recovery Center, we begin drug and alcohol treatment with our detoxification program which is carried out in our JCAHO-Accredited detox facility by our competent and caring staff. \nWhat detox cannot do\n\nDetox is primarily designed to cleanse the body and to prepare it for recovery. It does not address the underlying causes of alcoholism or drug addiction nor produce lasting changes in behaviors. Successful detox involves other treatment programs that will deal with the psychological process, behaviors and social functions involved in your alcoholism and addiction.\n\n<h2>SOBA Malibu Detox Process</h2>\n\nAt SOBA Malibu Los Angeles detox center, we deal with every aspect of your addiction. We initiate the treatment through our state of the art detox facility to remove the harmful side effects of the substances in your body. It is followed by series of treatments designed to heal your mind and to get to the bottom of your addictive behaviors. We have celebrated specialists to address all the issues that affect your condition like physicians, psychiatrists, therapists, counselors and other equally competent staff. \n\nWe also offer our well-structured alcohol and drug treatment program in a relaxed and luxurious beachfront setting. There are also other healing activities like art and music therapy, ropes courses, surf therapy and other fun and refreshing activities. You can also welcome each day with optimism as you are greeted by the beautiful sunrise or you can unwind in warm afternoons while gazing at the marvelous sunset. You can bring your pet and stay in our beautifully designed beach cottages called, Sobanas and experience 24/7 nursing care and excellent food service from our kitchen staff. \n\nCall us at 866-547-6451 for more details on drug and alcohol detox process and seven day detox.\n','Los Angeles Detox Center','','publish','closed','closed','','los-angeles-detox-center','','','2012-10-09 09:20:32','2012-10-09 09:20:32','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?page_id=1279',11,'page','',0),(1284,1,'2012-10-11 02:10:47','2012-10-11 02:10:47','Drug addiction and alcohol dependence can lead to serious and sometimes fatal conditions. Addictive substances disrupt the normal reactions of the brain especially the reward system. As the person continuously uses the drugs, the body requires more dosage to trigger the reward response. There is already an increased tolerance to the quantity of drugs and in the long run, the person develops dependence to the drugs. \n\n<h2>Common drug and alcohol withdrawal symptoms</h2>\nWhen a person decides to quit, the body will not easily tolerate the absence of drugs. This results to uncomfortable or serious withdrawal symptoms.\nThe following are the most common withdrawal signs:\n<ul>\n<li>Exhaustion or fatigue</li>\n<li>Lack of energy</li>\n<li>Depression,</li>\n<li>Anxiety</li>\n<li>Insomnia</li>\n<li>Oversleeping</li>\n<li>Nausea and vomiting</li>\n<li>Increased perspiration</li>\n<li>Clammy hands and feet</li>\n<li>Pallor</li>\n<li>Teary eyes</li>\n<li>Runny nose</li>\n<li>Overeating</li>\n<li>Appetite loss</li>\n<li>Diarrhea or loose bowel movement</li>\n<li>Headaches</li>\n<li>Irritability </li>\n<li>Mood swings</li>\n<li>Muscle pain</li>\n<li>Rapid heart rate</li>\n<li>Sexual dysfunction</li>\n<li>Tremors or shaking</li>\n</ul>\n\nSerious withdrawal symptoms that need immediate medical assistance include the following:\n<ul>\n<li>Agitation</li>\n<li>Black outs: A person forgets what happened while drinking</li> \n<li>Convulsions</li> \n<li>Fever</li>\n<li>Hallucinations</li>\n<li>Seizures</li>\n<li>Severe confusion</li>\n</ul>\n\nMedically supervised detox program removes the injurious effects of the substances in the person’s body. It shall also gradually restore the normal functions of the brain which has become adapted to the presence of these addictive substances. \n\n<h2>Qualities of a good detox center</h2>\n\nAn effective medically supervised detox program like seven day drug detox should be carried out in a high-quality detox facility. The following are the characteristics of a good detox center:\nIt must be recommended by a medical professional: Consult your doctor or a medical professional before you register in any detox facility. It is important to seek advice from someone who can explain to you the process of detoxification, its importance and effects. At SOBA Malibu, we have certified counselors to talk to you 24/7 through our hotline: 866-547-6451.\n\nIt must be accredited. There are many detox centers in the country and not all of them are certified. SOBA Recovery center’s detox facility is JCAHO-Accredited. We are proud to claim that our state of the art facility is hygienic, safe and comfortable. It is also managed by competent and caring staff.\n\nIt should be covered by your insurance: Detox procedures can be costly without it. You should check with your health insurance provider if the detox facility you have chosen is accepted by your health plan. At SOBA Malibu, we offer assistance in insurance verification and we also guide you in determining the cost of our detox services and residence facility. You can simply fill-out our form in the insurance verification page. \n\nIt must have an individualized treatment program suited to your addiction: The SOBA method uses an individually-tailored treatment plan for our detox patients. We use the holistic treatment approach composed of detoxification, behavioral and psychological programs, and nutrition and fitness plan. We also have other types of healing therapies designed to speed up your recovery process like experiential therapy, educational groups, individual groups and 12-step work.\nFor more information on medically supervised seven day detox and other treatment programs, call us at 866-547-6451.\n','Seven Day Detox','','publish','closed','closed','','seven-day-detox','','','2012-10-11 02:10:47','2012-10-11 02:10:47','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?page_id=1284',10,'page','',0),(1288,1,'2012-10-11 02:17:28','2012-10-11 02:17:28','<div style=\"width:700px;padding:10px;margin:5px;\">\n<h2>Los Angeles Rapid Detox</h2>\n\nIf you are searching for the most effective inpatient drug rehab and seven day detox, SOBA Malibu Los Angeles Rapid Detox is the ideal choice. It follows strict standards to perform this cutting-edge process and it ensures safety and wellness of its patients. Additionally SOBA Malibu is an inpatient drug rehab that provides a holistic method to boost the possibility of your full recovery.\n\n<h2>Common seven day detox issues</h2>\n\nWhile some people think that detox is an easy procedure that can be performed by anyone, rapid detox is not like the self-detox kits that anybody can carry out. The usual rapid detox starts with a supervised infusion of substances that puts a patient to sleep and allows the elimination of toxins from the body within ten hours. There are also problems associated with this procedure like the following:\n<ul>\n\n<li>The patient is not prepared for long-term recovery. Remember that detox only eliminates harmful chemicals from your body and reduces the physical signs of withdrawal. But, the emotional signs of withdrawal are still there. The patient is still an addict, only cleaner.  What a patient needs is a holistic approach that will address all issues involving his or her addiction. </li>\n\n<li>Very few insurance companies cover rapid detox procedures: Some insurance companies consider rapid detox as an experimental method that carries numerous risks. As a result, some patients are hesitant to undergo rapid detox for fear that they will not be sufficiently covered by their health insurance.</li> \n\n<li>It is costly: Many detox centers charge very high rates for rapid detox services. It is due to the fact that rapid detox entails the knowledge and skills of professional staff that will ensure the safety and effectiveness of the procedure. </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>How SOBA Malibu deals with common detox issues</h2>\n\nOn long term recovery: We, at SOBA Malibu inpatient drug rehab implement a three-step process to ensure recovery. We embark on your treatment process with our special detox services performed in our fully equipped facility which is JCAHO accredited.  Next, we manage your withdrawal symptoms through our professional and skilled staff. Finally, we nourish and strengthen your body. We have trained kitchen workers who prepare sumptuous food to help you regain your strength. Our fitness trainers shall also guide you in our fitness program to help you attain physical stability\nOn insurance options: We at SOBA would love to discuss with you the insurance options available. We have professional staff who will give you all the information you need with regards to insurance issues.\n\nOn detox cost: In spite of the fact that our detox facility is managed by highly skilled professionals, SOBA Malibu Los Angeles rapid detox services are available at very reasonable rates. You can also talk to our phone counselors to learn more about our payment alternatives. \n\nWe are willing to provide you with cost-effective and helpful detox services that will help you achieve total recovery.\n\nTo learn more about our seven day detox and unique inpatient drug rehab programs, call us at 866-547-6451. \n</div>','Rapid Detox - Los Angeles Facility','','publish','closed','closed','','rapid-detox-los-angeles-facility','','','2012-10-11 02:17:28','2012-10-11 02:17:28','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?page_id=1288',9,'page','',0),(1291,1,'2012-10-11 19:35:26','2012-10-11 19:35:26','SOBA Malibu rehab is the finest sober living facility in Malibu that possesses all the important components of an effective alcohol and drug rehab. We take pride in our excellent facilities, prestigious team of experts, unique treatment approach and natural beachfront setting. Everything that composes SOBA drug rehab Malibu is designed to increase your chance for a successful recovery. \n\n<h2>When choosing a rehab, you should look for the following features:</h2>\n\n<ol>\n<li>Early diagnosis of drug addiction. You have a great chance to recover if your condition is detected early. SOBA Malibu rehab has effective initial screening and evaluation procedures to detect early signs of addiction.</li> \n<li>Individualized treatment method: It takes a distinctive approach to understand the root cause of your addiction and the prevailing factors that affect your recovery. These factors include:</li>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Gender</li> \n<li>Severity of addiction</li>\n<li>Motivation to recover</li>\n<li>Presence of co-occurring disorders</li>\n<li>Withdrawal signs: A drug addict has the tendency to return to drug use in order to relieve the painful signs of withdrawal.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<li>Contingency management: It takes self-discipline to break away from the clutches of addiction. SOBA treatment method is just a big hand which is willing to pull you out from the mire of addiction and to guide you until you fully recover. But, the decision to stop being an addict should come from you. With this in mind, we at SOBA Malibu rehab observe behavior contracting technique to reward your positive behaviors and to punish negative ones. This unique reward and punishment system has been proven as a successful method of increasing positive treatment outcomes.</li> \n\n<li>Behavioral skills: Addicts and non-addicts have to face everyday situations that may trigger stress or other emotional outbursts. At SOBA, we will help you learn life skills and stress reduction techniques, based on cognitive behavioral therapy and other treatment philosophies.</li>\n\n<li>Continuing care: We provide follow-up services after you leave SOBA rehab in Malibu. We also have a very active support groups to encourage you stick to your recovery goals.</li>\n\n<li>Dedicated staff: At SOBA, we serve our patients with our hands and heart. It is our objective to see you completely well.</li> \n</ol>\n\n<h2>Unique SOBA Professional Support system</h2>\n\nAt SOBA drug rehab Malibu, we have professional staff to help you in every step of the way. We have licensed addictionologist, psychiatrist and clinical psychologist to take care of your addiction behavior, co-occurring disorders and causative factors of your addiction. Our acupuncturist, hypnotherapist, and personal trainer will help you achieve physical fitness and stable body. Your nutritionist and wellness coach shall also make sure that your body is well-nourished and equipped for daily activities. You and your family shall also learn how to deal with your condition and to prevent relapse through the help of our marriage and family therapist and our discharge and aftercare planner.\n\nCall us at 866-547-6451 for more details on the features of SOBA Malibu rehab and our unique services. \n','Malibu Recovery Center','','publish','closed','closed','','malibu-recovery-center','','','2012-10-11 19:35:26','2012-10-11 19:35:26','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?page_id=1291',8,'page','',0),(1295,1,'2012-10-12 19:54:53','2012-10-12 19:54:53','<a href=\"http://www.sobamalibu.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/malibu_rehab.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-1513\" alt=\"Malibu Rehab\" src=\"http://www.sobamalibu.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/malibu_rehab.jpg\" /></a>If you finally decide to seek help for your drug addiction, SOBA Malibu Rehab is the best place to be. Its unique treatment method and holistic approach surpass any drug rehab in Malibu. SOBA also takes pride in its modern and high-quality detox service which is also better than any detox in Malibu.\nReasons for not entering a drug detox and drug rehab\n\nMany individuals struggle with drug addiction for several years because they think they can get sober on their own. Others are ashamed to ask for help because of fear of rejection and criticism. Some are afraid of things to come right after calling a drug rehab in Malibu, or a detox in Malibu. We at SOBA Malibu understand these inner struggles and we applaud your courage in seeking for assistance. It reflects your inner strength in admitting your inability to control your addiction and courage to undergo whatever it takes for you to recover.\n\n<h2>Facility Tour</h2>\n\n[gallery ids=\"1521,1525,1526,1529,1530,1531,1533,1535,1537\"]\n\n<a href=\"http://www.sobamalibu.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/soba200.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.sobamalibu.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/soba200-250x121.jpg\" alt=\"soba200\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1517\" /></a>\n\n<h2>Signs that you need detox and rehab</h2>\n\nDetox in Malibu can be your first step to deal with your addiction. SOBA Recovery center is a drug rehab in Malibu that can give you the best access to the path of recovery. But when should you reach out for help? The following are signs that you need a hand to lift you from the bondage of addiction:\n\nTolerance: You have to increase the dosage of the drug just to get the same level of “high” or stimulation since the first time you took it. For instance- you used to take one capsule to get “drugged”. Now you are taking 4 capsules before feeling any effect.\n\nPhysical signs of withdrawal: You experience withdrawal symptoms since your last dose. Some of the most common signs of withdrawal include:\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Tremors</li>\n	<li>Tachycardia or rapid heart rate</li>\n	<li>Sweating</li>\n	<li>Seizures</li>\n	<li>Runny nose</li>\n	<li>Nausea and vomiting</li>\n	<li>Insomnia</li>\n	<li>Increased blood pressure</li>\n	<li>Hallucinations</li>\n	<li>Fever: It is a dangerous sign of withdrawal. You need to go to the nearest hospital when you exceed your normal body temperature.</li>\n	<li>Cramps</li>\n	<li>Confusion</li>\n	<li>Chills</li>\n	<li>Body pains</li>\n</ul>\n\nUnintended drugging: You don’t settle for small doses anymore. Though you just wanted to take a small shot, you end up taking more than what you intended.\n\nDrug preoccupation: The drug becomes your life. You are no longer interested in other things because getting “high” is your priority. This could lead to job loss, poor grades or broken relationships.\n\nMultiple drug use: You explore other drugs either to get wasted or to control your withdrawal symptoms.\nRefusal to enter a rehab: Your family or friends may have tried to convince you to enter a rehab but you refuse to do so. You may have researched about it but you are afraid to give it a try. Or, you have apprehensions about the drug rehab program.\n\n<h2>Invitation from SOBA Malibu</h2>\n\nThe road to recovery is not easy but SOBA Recovery Center-a drug rehab in Malibu would like to help you take the first step. Let us know that you accept our offer to help you .Make a phone call right now at 866-547-6451.','SOBA Recovery Center Malibu Rehab','','publish','closed','closed','','malibu-rehab','','','2012-10-12 19:54:53','2012-10-12 19:54:53','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?page_id=1295',7,'page','',0),(1301,1,'2012-11-08 19:48:25','2012-11-08 19:48:25','<h3>If you think that conventional drug rehab does not produce the recovery you expect because it does not deal with dual diagnosis of addiction, you can try SOBA Malibu. Aside from our holistic and individualized treatment programs aimed to help alcoholics and drug addicts to recover from addiction, we also concentrate on co-existing conditions like depression and offer a unique dual diagnosis treatment program. We take into consideration underlying causes of your condition as well as the external factors that trigger bipolar disorder.</h3>\n<h2>External triggers of bipolar disorder</h2>\nThe following are the external factors that trigger bipolar disorder:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Issues at home</li>\n 	<li>Relationship problems</li>\n 	<li>Seasonal conditions: Bipolar disorder is influenced by cold weather especially winter</li>\n 	<li>Serious emotional pressure</li>\n 	<li>Work-related stress</li>\n 	<li>Drug addiction. Bipolar disorder is triggered by the use of drugs particularly cocaine, meth and other stimulants.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Problems in bipolar treatment for drug addicts</h3>\nBipolar disorder is not easily treated because of the following reasons:\n\nLate detection: A person with bipolar disorder does not readily notice that he or she is suffering from the condition. Bipolar symptoms like hyperactivity and depression are often associated to normal mood swings due to weather conditions, situations at home or work and the like. A person often recognizes that there is a problem when he or she already experiences problems related to the condition.\n\nDenial: Oftentimes, a person with bipolar suffers from denial of illness. This is the characteristic symptom of bipolar disorder and drug addiction. Such denial swings during the course of the condition and makes detection and rehabilitation very difficult due to refusal of treatment.\n\nMisdiagnosis: People suffering from drug addiction may also exhibit signs similar to bipolar disorder. As a result of the similarity of symptoms, the person may be over-diagnosed with bipolar. Therefore, it is crucial for a dual diagnosis treatment center to employ the best staff to ensure proper judgment.\n\nAbsence of FDA approved drug to treat drug addiction and bipolar simultaneously: At present, the drug of choice for bipolar patients is lithium. But, recent studies showed that drug abuse decreases the effects of this drug to bipolar patients. Therefore, excellent medical treatment and careful medical management are indispensable in the success of rehabilitation.\n<h3>The SOBA bipolar rehab way of managing dual diagnosis</h3>\nWe at SOBA <a href=\"http://www.sobamalibu.com\">bipolar rehab</a> recognize the need for individualized treatment for patients with dual diagnosis. Our team of experts shall organize a wide array of therapies to deal with your addiction issues and bipolar disorder. The specialized team of professionals shall include the medical team which shall take care of your total well-being. The team is composed of the following:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Addictionologist</li>\n 	<li>Clinical psychologist</li>\n 	<li>Marriage and family therapist</li>\n 	<li>Psychiatrist</li>\n</ul>\nSince we are a <a href=\"http://www.sobamalibu.com/treatment-programs/holisitic-treatment-explained/\">holistic rehab</a>, we also provide additional therapies to heal your mind, body and spirit with the help of the following individuals:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Acupuncturist</li>\n 	<li>Discharge and aftercare planner</li>\n 	<li>Hypnotherapist</li>\n 	<li>Nutrition and wellness coach</li>\n 	<li>Personal trainer</li>\n</ul>\nCall us at (866)-547-6451 for immediate help.','SOBA Malibu Dual Diagnosis','','publish','closed','closed','','soba-malibu-dual-diagnosis','','','2012-11-08 19:48:25','2012-11-08 19:48:25','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?p=1301',7,'post','',0),(1306,1,'2012-11-19 02:10:47','2012-11-19 02:10:47','<p class=\"lead\">OxyContin is classified as an opioid agonist due to its Oxycodone content which is a Schedule II drug. It is prescribed for a continuous and long-term management of moderate to severe pain for patients with an established tolerance to an opiate of equivalent potency. Statistics showed that it is one of the most commonly used prescription drugs in the country. In a <a href=\"http://www.drugabuse.gov/publications/topics-in-brief/prescription-drug-abuse\">study</a> conducted by NIDA in 2010, 5.1% of the students in 12th grade abused OxyContin.</p>\n\n<h3>How oxycontin affects your health depends on dosage, drug administration, and existing medical conditions. The following are the effects of Oxycontin on major body systems:</h3>\n<strong>Nervous System</strong>\n\nThe common side effects of Oxycontin to the CNS include:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Drowsiness</li>\n 	<li>Sedation</li>\n 	<li>Dizziness</li>\n 	<li>Headache</li>\n 	<li>Dry mouth</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>For patients with Addison’s disease</strong>\n\nDoctors exercise caution in prescribing Oxycontin to individuals with Adrenal insufficiency because <strong>administration of this drug can cause the following</strong>:\n\nRespiratory depression\nIncreases the possibility of prolonged CNS depression related to opioid use\nFor patients with brain injury\n\nMechanical ventilation is required before opiate agonists like Oxycontin can be administered. Otherwise, oxycontin will cause hypoventilation that induces vasodilation and cerebral hypoxia. As a result, the patient may experience the following:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Increased intracranial pressure</li>\n 	<li>Alteration in the CNS functions including consciousness, pupil movements and respiration</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Gastrointestinal</strong>\n\nSome of the usual <strong>side effects of Oxycontin on the GI tract</strong> include the following:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Constipation</li>\n 	<li>Nausea</li>\n 	<li>Vomiting</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>For patients with colon cancer and esophageal cancer</strong>\nPatients may complain of:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Difficulty in swallowing Oxycontin tablet</li>\n 	<li>Intestinal obstruction</li>\n 	<li>Exacerbation of diverticulitis</li>\n 	<li>For patients with Impaired GI motility</li>\n</ul>\nOxycontin decreases peristalsis and increases the smooth muscle tone in the gastrointestinal tract. As a result, the patient may experience:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Elevated intraluminal pressure</li>\n 	<li>Spasm</li>\n 	<li>Constipation</li>\n 	<li>Toxic megacolon for individuals suffering from acute or severe inflammatory bowel disease due to the decrease in the motility of the colon</li>\n 	<li>Aggravates symptoms of infectious diarrhea</li>\n</ul>\nRespiratory\n\nRapid administration or high dosage of oxycontin may cause:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Apnea</li>\n 	<li>Anoxia</li>\n 	<li>Chronic pulmonary insufficiency</li>\n 	<li>Hypercapnia</li>\n 	<li>Hypoxia</li>\n 	<li>Rigidity of respiratory muscles</li>\n 	<li>Sleep apnea</li>\n 	<li>Upper airway obstruction</li>\n</ul>\nHepatic\n\nOxycontin is significantly metabolized by the liver. Its serum concentration may be increased in patients with a liver condition.\n\nCardiovascular\n\nAt a therapeutic dosage, Oxycontin may cause:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Dizziness</li>\n 	<li>Hypotension</li>\n</ul>\nIf administered rapidly or in elevated dosage, it can lead to:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Cardiac arrest</li>\n 	<li>Shock</li>\n 	<li>Vasodilatation</li>\n</ul>\nDue to the cholinergic activity of Oxycontin, its increased dosage or rapid administration may produce the following:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Arrhythmia</li>\n 	<li>Bradycardia</li>\n</ul>\nRenal\n\nPatients with renal impairment may alter the elimination of Oxycontin and its metabolites which may result to the following:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Drug accumulation</li>\n 	<li>Greater risk of toxicity</li>\n</ul>\nPsychiatric\n\nSome of the withdrawal effects of Oxycontin include:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Agitation</li>\n 	<li>Anxiety</li>\n 	<li>Hallucinations</li>\n 	<li>Paranoia</li>\n 	<li>Psychosis</li>\n 	<li>Restlessness</li>\n</ul>\nIn spite of Oxycontin’s adverse effects, statistics showed that almost 1 in 20 high school seniors abused OxyContin. NSDUH also estimated that approximately 1.9 million individuals in the country abuse or suffer from chemical dependence on prescription opioids.\n\nFor more information on how oxycontin affects your health, contact the nearest addiction specialist in your area.\n\nReferences:\n<a href=\"http://dailymed.nlm.nih.gov/dailymed/drugInfo.cfm?id=71915\">http://dailymed.nlm.nih.gov/dailymed/drugInfo.cfm?id=71915</a>\n<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmedhealth/PMH0000589/\">http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmedhealth/PMH0000589/</a>\n<a href=\"http://www.drugabuse.gov/publications/topics-in-brief/prescription-drug-abuse\">http://www.drugabuse.gov/publications/topics-in-brief/prescription-drug-abuse</a>','Health Effects Of Oxycontin','','publish','closed','closed','','health-effects-of-oxycontin','','','2012-11-19 02:10:47','2012-11-19 02:10:47','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?p=1306',6,'post','',0),(1310,1,'2012-12-06 08:02:42','2012-12-06 08:02:42','<p class=\"lead\">When you finally decided to get ahead of your life and quit drugs or alcohol, you took your initial step towards recovery. However, you may have thought that all your anticipated problems will go away when you enter a rehab, only to find out that a bunch of them are still there. You can have mixed feelings about changing your old circle of friends, and you can also feel doubtful about your commitment to stay sober. However, it is important to bear in mind that recovery is a major life decision that takes time. It involves <a href=\"http://www.sobamalibu.com\">relapse prevention</a> planning so that you can keep your goals. This article shall discuss about relapse and the importance of aftercare and sober living after drug rehab.</p>\n\n<h2>What is <strong>Relapse</strong>?</h2>\nRelapse occurs when you slip back to old patterns of behavior or habits. It does not necessarily mean that you have to take drugs or drink again after quitting for a while. Relapse may begin when you think that you can control drug or alcohol use and you take a chance to use it again. Some relapse triggers may also include the following:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Poor stress management of problems related to work, school or family situations. When crisis or stresses build up, some people go back to alcohol and drug use.</li>\n 	<li>Failing to address your legal, medical or financial problems. You must not only solve the problems, but you also have to deal with your stress.</li>\n 	<li>You give in to your alcohol and drug cravings.</li>\n 	<li>You no longer stick to your recovery plan. You may have missed several AA meetings or meeting with your support groups.</li>\n 	<li>When stressed, you immediately think of drinking or using drugs again to cope up with it. You no longer want to deal with your loneliness, boredom and other negative emotions using the life skills you learned in the rehab or sober living facility.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>What is <strong>relapse prevention</strong>?</h2>\n<a href=\"http://www.sobamalibu.com\">Detox and treatment programs</a> may not be enough to establish complete and continuing recovery. You need to learn a new lifestyle, through relapse prevention planning. In a nutshell, you need a guide to your new life without drugs or alcohol. Achieving sobriety is only a baby step towards full recovery. You need to grow as a person and you can only achieve this through a personal evaluation of you entire life and a development of a long-term plan for your total recovery. After rehab, relapse prevention plan aimed to achieving long-term changes shall follow.\n\nA good aftercare program and sober living facility shall help you learn skills that will allow you to stick to your relapse prevention plan. Planning revolves around there major components:\n\n<strong>People involved in your recovery:</strong> Your sponsor, counselor, family and friends. Family members and friends who also attend AA meetings or family therapy learn how to help the addict stay sober.\n\n<strong>Life skills and effective stress management techniques:</strong> It is important to know what triggers your relapse and how you can handle them. You will learn techniques on how to reduce your daily stress.\n\nKnow when to ask for help: Once you need help because you’re beginning to stay off track again you need to seek for it.','Relapse Prevention','','publish','closed','closed','','relapse-prevention','','','2012-12-06 08:02:42','2012-12-06 08:02:42','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?p=1310',5,'post','',0),(1319,1,'2013-01-20 08:11:22','2013-01-20 08:11:22','<p class=\"lead\">Detox success statistics are difficult to gauge because of the different characteristics of addictive substances and their effects on the users’ body and mind. True recovery does not end with the detox. It starts with it. Prevailing statistics proved how detox helps a person avoid relapse with the help of an effective and comprehensive addiction treatment program.</p>\n<h2>Statistics</h2>\nSAMSHA claimed that patients who undergo detoxification as part of their addiction treatment will not readily relapse compared to their counterparts who did not go through detox. In addition, it will take 40% longer for patients who completed a comprehensive 30-day detox to relapse. This is a significant rate that shows detox success. However, detox itself will not cure addiction. The 2006 SAMSHA study proved that 25% of patients who went through detox are readmitted within the same year for substance abuse detox. But, patients who underwent detox as part f their substance abuse treatment program have an increased probability of recovery. The study also stressed the importance of attending an immediate addiction treatment program right after detoxification to avoid relapse.\n<h2>Detox mechanism</h2>\nIt is important to note that substance abuse has deleterious effects on a person’s brain and body. When a person tries to withdraw from using addictive substances the period of withdrawal ensues. Such period is described by painful and sometimes life-threatening symptoms. In order for a person to safely get out of substance abuse, detoxification is necessary. Consequently, a good treatment program for drug addiction starts with a comprehensive detox which aims to achieve medical stability.\n<h3>Detox success is attained through the following means:</h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Gradual reduction of drug or alcohol dose</li>\n 	<li>Substitution of a similar or alternative drug with lesser side-effects</li>\n</ul>\nAlthough some individuals may not need medical supervision during the detoxification period, it is vital to undergo detox in a specialized facility to ensure the patient’s safety. Generally, the detox process requires the following medical assistance:\n\n<strong>Monitoring of vital signs:</strong> Detox is a crucial procedure that aims to expel the chemicals from your system. During detox, you cannot take addictive drugs. This implies the fact that your body will feel symptoms associated with your withdrawal from addictive substances. Some signs of withdrawal may include changes in vital signs which can be indicative of a life-threatening condition. Examples of vital sign changes that require prompt medical attention include the following:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Temperature: Hot flashes, mild fever and hypothermia (decreased body temperature)</li>\n 	<li>Pulse: Increased/decreased pulse rate</li>\n 	<li>Respiration: Rapid breathing (hyperventilation) or decreased breathing (hypoventilation)&gt;</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Blood pressure:</strong> Hypertension or hypotension may indicate a serious medical condition that requires quick medical intervention.\n\n<strong>Emotional support:</strong> There are counselors and therapists available to help the patients discuss their fears and worries with regards to the detox procedure and the ordeals of addiction treatment. Presence of loved ones especially family members of close friends are also helpful in motivating the patient to carry on with the treatment.\n\n<strong>Medications:</strong> If it is necessary, medications shall be administered by the qualified medical personnel assigned to you.\n\nVisit the nearest <a href=\"http://www.sobamalibu.com\">Los Angeles detox center</a> to know more about detox success statistics and the suitable detox and addiction treatment for you or your loved one.\n\nReferences:\n<a href=\"http://www.samhsa.gov/newsroom/advisories/0611162305.aspx\">http://www.samhsa.gov/newsroom/advisories/0611162305.aspx</a>\n<a href=\"http://www.csam-asam.org/sites/default/files/pdf/misc/TIP_45.pdf\">http://www.samhsa.gov/newsroom/advisories/0611162305.aspx</a>','Detox : The First Step In Addiction Treatment','','publish','closed','closed','','detox-the-first-step-in-addiction-treatment','','','2013-01-20 08:11:22','2013-01-20 08:11:22','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?p=1319',4,'post','',0),(1341,1,'2013-04-24 07:12:19','2013-04-24 07:12:19','','sidebar-badges','','inherit','closed','closed','','sidebar-badges','','','2013-04-24 07:12:19','2013-04-24 07:12:19','',0,'http://soba.localhost.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/sidebar-badges.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1386,1,'2013-04-24 08:15:52','2013-04-24 08:15:52','Dr. Modir is one of the most recognized and respected physicians in the addiction recovery field, and is known for the effectiveness of her holistic approach to treatment. She completed residency training in Psychiatry at Harbor-UCLA Medical Center and sub-specialty training in Addiction Psychiatry at the UCLA Medical Center. Dr. Modir is also a Diplomate of the American Board of Psychiatry and Neurology for Addiction Psychiatry, and has extensive training in Dialectical Behavioral Therapy (DBT) and Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT). Dr. Modir is also a licensed buprenorphine provider.','Shahla Modir, M.D. Independently Affiliated Physician','','publish','closed','closed','','shahla-modir','','','2013-04-24 08:15:52','2013-04-24 08:15:52','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?post_type=staff&amp;p=1386',8,'staff','',0),(1387,1,'2013-04-24 08:18:39','2013-04-24 08:18:39','Sherry Gaba, LCSW, is a licensed psychotherapist and life coach who has helped hundreds of people cope with lifelong addictions, including substance abuse, shopping, gambling, food, sex and love, co-dependency, trauma, depression, anxiety, single parenting and divorce. Sherry appeared on Celebrity Rehab 3, 4, and 5.   She also facilitated life coaching on their subsequent spin off Sober House and Celebrity Rehab’s Sex Addiction. During filming of the series, Sherry used her trademark sensitivity and compassion to help troubled cast members as they transitioned into their new sober lives with psychotherapy and life coaching tips.  Sherry most recently appeared on CNN Headline News as a guest expert, as well as Inside Edition, where she spoke about Mackenzie Phillips who was on Celebrity Rehab 3.  In addition, she appeared on KTLA Channel 5 as an expert on eating disorders and Fox San Diego News, Better TV, WPIX New York, CNN Prime News, Issues with Jane Velez Mitchell on HLN, Showbiz Tonight, Joy Behar on HLN, the Bio Channel: The Tragic Side of Fame and E!News discussing Celebrity Rehab and Teen Mom on MTV.  Sherry’s book, “The Law of Sobriety” from HCI Publications is about recovery from addictions and alcoholism and was published in September 2010.  Sherry has also been published in Cosmopolitan Magazine, Women’s World, Los Angeles Times Blog, New York Post, The Huffington Post, Hollywood Life, Elle On-line, E! On-line, Radar On-line and the New York Daily News.  She has also been a guest with Martha Stewart, Jay Thomas, and Judith Regan on Sirius XM Radio.  Sherry also blogs on Beliefnet.com, Counselor Magazine,  and Deepak Chopra’s IntentBlog.com,  In addition she was a host on CBS Sky Radio of  “A Moment of Change,” a show on self discovery and positive transformation and now co-hosts the Kim Pagano Radio Show in Ventura, CA.\n\nWith over fifteen years of experience as a clinician, Sherry has worked at some of the top rehabilitation centers around such as the famed Promises Treatment Center in Malibu.   Though presently she works at Soba Recovery Center, Sherry currently dedicates most of her time to her private practice in Westlake Village, CA and her media career. Sherry is passionate about helping her clients with a supportive approach to help them resolve problems and change long-standing patterns. \n\nBorn and raised in the San Fernando Valley (Van Nuys), California, Sherry had to learn the art of problem solving at a young age. At 26, she became a single mother.  She had just graduated from college with a Journalism degree and was not able to pursue her passion for television and radio news to focus on raising her daughter. Once her daughter was old enough, Sherry made the choice to go back to school and entered a master’s program and received her Masters of Social Work from the prestigious University of Southern California. Sherry is also an expert and published author on the subjects of parenting, single parenting, divorce, and relationships.  She is a contributing author to the book “Chicken Soup For the Soul: Tough Times Tough People” which highlights how a person can follow their dreams and succeed as Sherry has highlighting her struggles from single parenting to a successful media expert, psychotherapist, and life coach. \n\nFor More information about Sherry Gaba, LCSW go to www.sherrygaba.com or contact her at sherry@sgabatherapy.com.   \n','Sherry Gaba, LCSW and Life Coach','','publish','closed','closed','','sherry-gaba','','','2013-04-24 08:18:39','2013-04-24 08:18:39','',0,'http://www.sobamalibu.com/?post_type=staff&amp;p=1387',7,'staff','',0),(1390,1,'2013-04-24 08:22:19','2013-04-24 08:22:19','<p>Andrea graduated from Los Angeles Southwest College, with an Associate Degree in Nursing. Her number one priority at Soba Recovery Center is our clients and their recovery. She works closely with admissions and and the physicians to insure that the clients receive a thorough and safe admission, as well as, discharge. &nbsp;