01:54:05','2017-08-23 01:54:05','','background-image_7','','inherit','closed','closed','','background-image_7','','','2017-08-23 01:54:05','2017-08-23 01:54:05','',0,'http://soba.localhost.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/background-image_7.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(2021,1,'2017-08-23 07:12:58','2017-08-23 07:12:58','Content goes here\n\n[gravityform id=\"9\" title=\"false\" description=\"false\" ajax=\"true\"]','Seeking Help For A Loved One?','','publish','closed','closed','','seeking-help-loved-one','','','2017-08-23 07:12:58','2017-08-23 07:12:58','',0,'http://dev.sobamalibu.com/?page_id=2021',0,'page','',0),(2030,1,'2017-12-14 18:40:31','2017-12-14 18:40:31','<p class=\"lead\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-2086\" src=\"http://dev.sobamalibu.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/IMG_5118_resize-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" />SOBA Recovery Center is a Residential Primary Drug and Alcohol Treatment Program, which includes medically-supervised detoxification. We are licensed and certified by the State of California Department of Alcohol and Drug Programs and the Joint Commission. The SOBA Recovery Center deploys a neuro-biological approach in order to accelerate the restoration and stabilization of the brain chemistry, and revitalize the body\'s natural reward system. We have psycho-therapy groups, experiential therapy, educational groups, individual therapy and 12-Step work to build a solid foundation for long-term recovery.</p>\n\n<h2>Assessment</h2>\n<p class=\"lead\">Anyone who suffers from addiction to alcohol or drugs has a unique set of circumstances. In other words, we have found time and time again that, \"one size doesn\'t fit all.\"</p>\nEach person has family relationships, livelihoods, upbringings, socio-economic backgrounds, and experiences that are unique in nature. More importantly, our entire treatment team knows from years of research that the physical ailments may also contribute to addiction and/or alcoholism. As a result, a detailed assessment is performed for the development of an individualized treatment plan by the treatment team.\n\nDuring the assessment process, a biopsycho social profile is created and a primary therapist is assigned for the entire length of the clients stay with us.\n<h2>Detox</h2>\n<p class=\"lead\">Although some individuals may not believe they need medical supervision during the detoxification period, it is vital to undergo supervised detox ensure the client’s safety.</p>\nDetox is a crucial procedure that aims to expel the chemicals from the individuals system.  Some signs of withdrawal may include changes in vital signs which can be indicative of a life-threatening condition and as a result detox should never be attempted unsupervised.  Depending on the type of substance the client has been abusing, detox can take anywhere from 7 days to 20 days.\n\nOur unique detox system is monitored by some of the best clinicians in Southern California, and utilizes cutting edge techniques to make the process as safe and comfortable as possible.\n\nOur counselors and therapists available to help client\'s discuss their fears and worries with regards to the detox procedure and the ordeals of addiction treatment. Presence of loved ones especially family members of close friends are also helpful in motivating the patient to carry on with the treatment.\n<h2>Residential Treatment</h2>\n<p class=\"lead\">SOBA Recovery Center provides and recommends a 90 day program. Residential Treatment is at our primary treatment location in Malibu, while transitional living is at one of our extended care facilities which continues many of the techniques learned in the primary phase.</p>\nFor clients unable to stay for the full 90 days, we are able to offer other options, including the use of sober coaches/companions and remote teleconferencing with our licensed therapists.\n<h3>We utilize evidence based practices in our treatment protocols, including:</h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li>CBT</li>\n 	<li>DBT</li>\n 	<li>Motivational Interviewing</li>\n 	<li>Seeking Safety</li>\n 	<li>Mindfulness</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Additional Services:</h3>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Yoga and Meditation</li>\n 	<li>Chiropractic Care</li>\n 	<li>Registered Dietician</li>\n 	<li>Accupuncture</li>\n 	<li><strong>And more...</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Location</h2>\n<p class=\"lead\">Our residential program and detox center is located on the sun-drenched shores of Malibu Beach, California. The transitional living programs are located near the beaches of Point Dume in Malibu, and the Pacific Palisades.</p>\nWe believe that our program location offers various healing properties. The overall feel and experience from endless sunshine and ocean to sunsets and the fresh breeze, aids in the process of recovery. You are nourished from land to facility at every angle of your treatment journey, which offers the complete approach to healing.\n\nOur detox and residential facilities and steps from the beach and offer amenities including Wifi, private rooms and flat screen TV\'s.\n[gallery ids=\"2088,2087,2089,2091,2092,2093,2094,2086,2065\"]\n<h2>Dual Diagnosis and Co-Occurring Disorder Treatment</h2>\nIn conjunction with the staff of the Cedars-Sinai\'s Department of Psychiatry and Behavioral Neurosciences, SOBA Recovery Center offers a wide range of services to maintain and ensure mental health. We treat all types of mental illnesses, and we develop strategies to enhance mental health in our community. Working closely with staff at Cedars-Sinai Medical Center and their world-renowned teaching facility, we are also deeply involved in training and research to insure SOBA clients receive the best chance at their recovery. The tradition of excellence at Cedars-Sinai is inspiring and SOBA\'s affiliation with some of their top medical professionals is inspiring. The scope of Cedars-Sinai\'s programs has placed them among the best in the country. Our patients receive the most complete, up-to-date mental health care possible.\n\nIn conjunction with our accomplished medical professionals, we understand that results must go beyond \"just believing\", the SOBA RECOVERY CENTER has quality improvement and review programs to measure our progress, and we weave our outcomes of Cedars-Sinai\'s staff research into the fabric of our daily practice. We constantly improve our programs, based on our own research and that of others. As a result, our patients can expect to receive real value from our services.','Detox & Residential','','publish','closed','closed','','detox-and-residential','','','2017-12-14 18:40:31','2017-12-14 18:40:31','',0,'http://dev.sobamalibu.com/?post_type=services&amp;p=2030',0,'services','',0),(2032,1,'2017-12-14 18:40:53','2017-12-14 18:40:53','<p class=\"lead\">The goal of SOBA Recovery Center is not only to create a safe and stable environment for our clients, but it’s to prepare them for “life after treatment”. Having developed the foundations of a healthy body and mind as well as healthy decision making and behavior, clients enter Phase II and begin planning for the future.</p>\nIn Phase II, clients also begin to develop on their own autonomy. In addition to the clinical treatment they receive for drug and alcohol, they perform necessary daily and weekly functions; everything from shopping for their own food to taking part in leisure and adventure activities of their choosing. Alternatively, clients can also attend a 12-Step Programs of their choosing or alternative programs like SMART Recovery. Toward the end of this phase, the feelings of uneasiness and anxiety begin to be replaced by the excitement of the opportunities set before them.\n<h2><strong>PHASE II Resources and Treatment</strong></h2>\n<h2>Clinical Therapy</h2>\nClients in Phase II maintain access to weekly individual therapy sessions as well as attending group session. Psychiatric care and medication management services continue as needed, and individualized treatment modalities begin to tailor the growing needs of the individual in this crucial developmental period.\n<h2>Group Sessions</h2>\n<ul>\n 	<li><strong>Skills Development:</strong> development of a specified skill in relation to group topic (e.g. Communication, Relapse Prevention, Life Skills)</li>\n 	<li><strong>Support and Recovery:</strong> Our Support and Recovery Groups are focused on peers supporting, providing feedback and helping each other through relating, displaying empathy and understanding. Although each client as an individualized treatment plan created, we find that there are some underlying characteristic all clients relate with one another about.</li>\n 	<li><strong>Interpersonal Process Groups:</strong> These groups are focused on using peer groups as an opportunity for healing.  Our Interpersonal Process Groups are facilitated by our clinicians.</li>\n 	<li><strong>Problem-Solving:</strong> Cognitive restructuring is the basic method for change.</li>\n 	<li><strong>Creative/Expressive Groups:</strong>  Art Therapy, Music Therapy, Acting in Recovery.</li>\n 	<li><strong>Psychoeducational Groups:</strong> Structured group focused on enhancing client’s knowledge and providing resources.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Case Management</h2>\nCase Managers continue to seamlessly provide guidance to clients as progress from Phase I and act as the main point of contact for family members. This is the time to implement planning for career success through education and employment opportunities in the Los Angeles area, through the guidance and close development of each client’s needs.\n<h2>Support Staff</h2>\nOur support staff is ever present for clients. As the clients begin returning to their lives (either working, learning or volunteering in the local community) our support staff acts as a integral part of the transition. Our clients maintain access to support staff 24 hours a day through their length of treatment.\n\n[gallery link=\"none\" ids=\"2111,2109,2110,2107\"]','Day Treatment','','publish','closed','closed','','day-treatment','','','2017-12-14 18:40:53','2017-12-14 18:40:53','',0,'http://dev.sobamalibu.com/?post_type=services&amp;p=2032',0,'services','',0),(2033,1,'2017-12-14 18:41:03','2017-12-14 18:41:03','<p class=\"lead\">Our supportive living program prepares them for the lifelong work that is associated with living sober. Clients who achieve this level of responsibility have a new self-acceptance. They have come to understand and firmly believe in a new, fulfilling way of life. SOBA Recovery Center graduates are willing and ready to face any and all of life’s challenges. They’ve also learned that a continued process of overcoming these challenges is what it takes to lead the long and prosperous lives they desire.</p>\n\n<h2></h2>\n<h2>PHASE III: Resources and Treatment</h2>\n<h2>Clinical Therapy</h2>\nAt this point in treatment, the post-acute issues have been settled, and each member of our community has found stability and success in changing their life. Our treatment modalities allow for the therapeutic process to grow with the individual. The clinical therapy our clients receive is now able to address some of the more ongoing issues, and reach much deeper into developmental progress without disturbing the balance of everyday living. All of the resources available continue to be implemented until the successful completion of the program and client graduation.\n<h2>Case Management</h2>\nEvery client at SOBA Recovery Center is assigned a Case Manager upon arrival, and they maintain the continuity through each of the phases working closely with the same individual throughout their enrollment. Case Managers provide support and personalized guidance to each client, based on their specific working needs at each stage. Working closely with our clients and establishing a plan for continued sobriety support, education goals, rebuilding of family relationships and employment opportunities that is specific to the client, Phase III Case Management provides assistance with continued success, budgeting and ultimately discharge planning. For those enrolled in school, syllabus management and time management remain the primary focus while career development and life skills practice work best for others. Through this process, we provide our clients every tool for a successful transition to their new life after graduation.\n<h2>Education Planning</h2>\nIn addition to establishing education goals, academic advisement is provided from Case Managers and Clinical Therapists that help clients realize those goals. They help the client connect with or transfer to schools with great recovery programs. Our advisors also provide top down support at every level, setting our clients up with the best opportunities to realize their goals. Everything aspect is addressed from helping clients to choose essay topics and editing to accountability by tracking each client’s educational planner filled with their individual class schedule and assignments.\n<h2>Employment Training</h2>\nPersonal accountability is paramount for both educational and employment success and the process begins from day one at SOBA Recovery Center. While under our care, clients engage in multiple activities for work, education or volunteering. This process teaches our clients to balance a schedule, and sets them up for later opportunities; all of which are necessary for a true sober transition their new life after Graduation.\n<h2>Family Support Program</h2>\nThe disease of drug and alcohol addiction is a damaging one. It ravages the lives of the addicts, and it harms those close to them. SOBA Recovery Center provides support for the families of our clients throughout each phase of treatment. Families of clients who partake in our Family Support Program learn that their own healing process is just as important to their loved one’s recovery as the process the client undergoes. These family members who experience this transformation are filled with strength and hope. These experiences are encouraged and shared by these family members at family workshops and support groups available twice a month. As each client approaches the end of their stay during Phase III, the family dialogue begins about what the next step will be. Individual family sessions with our clients’ Clinical Therapists can be established to accurately plan for continued growth and success.\n\n[gallery ids=\"2111,2106,2109,2101,2102,2100\"]','Supportive Living','','publish','closed','closed','','supportive-living','','','2017-12-14 18:41:03','2017-12-14 18:41:03','',0,'http://dev.sobamalibu.com/?post_type=services&amp;p=2033',0,'services','',0),(2035,1,'2017-12-14 21:01:27','2017-12-14 21:01:27','Test','Test','','trash','closed','closed','','test__trashed','','','2017-12-14 21:01:27','2017-12-14 21:01:27','',0,'http://sobamalibu.localhost/?post_type=press&amp;p=1881',12,'press','',0),(2036,1,'2017-12-14 22:11:04','2017-12-14 22:11:04','','Another','','trash','closed','closed','','another__trashed','','','2017-12-14 22:11:04','2017-12-14 22:11:04','',0,'http://sobamalibu.localhost/?post_type=press&amp;p=1891',11,'press','',0),(2037,1,'2017-12-14 22:11:29','2017-12-14 22:11:29','','Another 2','','trash','closed','closed','','another-2__trashed','','','2017-12-14 22:11:29','2017-12-14 22:11:29','',0,'http://sobamalibu.localhost/?post_type=press&amp;p=1892',10,'press','',0),(2038,1,'2017-12-14 22:11:43','2017-12-14 22:11:43','','Another 3','','trash','closed','closed','','another-3__trashed','','','2017-12-14 22:11:43','2017-12-14 22:11:43','',0,'http://sobamalibu.localhost/?post_type=press&amp;p=1893',9,'press','',0),(2039,1,'2017-12-14 22:11:55','2017-12-14 22:11:55','','Another 4','','trash','closed','closed','','another-4__trashed','','','2017-12-14 22:11:55','2017-12-14 22:11:55','',0,'http://sobamalibu.localhost/?post_type=press&amp;p=1894',8,'press','',0),(2040,1,'2017-12-14 22:12:08','2017-12-14 22:12:08','','Another 5','','trash','closed','closed','','anothe